On Wednesday May 12th around 615 pm I started having symptoms of a stroke. I was scrambling my words, couldn?t talk right and my left side of my face wouldn?t move when I spoke or smiled. When I smiled my whole smile shifted to the right.  I had my girlfriend call 911 because I knew I was having a stroke. The symptoms lasted about 6 or 7 minutes. By the time the emt got there I was talking fine and my face was back to normal. I went to hospital where a cat scan was done on Wednesday night and came back fine. The doctors decided to admit me because they wanted me to get an MRI in the morning, which I did and came back that I had a minor stroke. The doctors think the stroke had something to with me being on an estrogen birth control as well as some family history but my primary care doctor recommend me report this because I did get the Jansen vaccine and it could have triggered what happened. I was discharged on Friday 5/14/2021 and I know have to take aspirin every day for the rest of my life, plavix for 21 days, and Lipitor until my doctor thinks I can come off.
LAB_DATA: Cat scan with dye was normal  MRI showed minor stroke, called a cerebrovascular accident  Ultrasound of both legs - came back normal  Ultrasound of heart - normal  Bubble test of heart to check for hole - normal  Full blood work up, tested my blood for any clotting conditions and still waiting for results from doctor.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client was feeling "cold." Client was a 14-year-old female sitting upright in her observation chair, alert and tracking with her eyes. Client had a chief complaint of dizziness and feeling cold.  Client stated that she began to feel cold and dizzy a few minutes after her observation had begun. This was the client's first dose of the Pfizer vaccine. Client denied any medical history or known allergies. Assessment revealed no swelling, hives, discoloration, shortness of breath or other signs and symptoms of anaphylaxis. Client stated that she felt "cold" and "dizzy." Client stated that her only meal was the snacks provided at the vaccination site. Airway, breathing and circulation were intact. Client's initial set of vitals at 1006 was 116/78 blood pressure, 80 heart rate, respirations 16, alert and oriented to person, place, date and event. Temperature 97.8*f. EMTs present were unable to obtain an O2 sat due to client's nail but client was negative for signs of shortness of breath. Client was asked to lie down until her complaint was resolved. Client was provided with food and was able to eat without difficulty. Client was reassessed every 15 minutes due to her stability. Vitals were as follows: 1011 - 108/78, 84, resp. 14 1021 108/78, 88, resp 14 1029 - 108/78, 80, resp 16. After approximately 10 minutes, the client denied any symptoms and was asked to sit up in an observation chair for the remainder of her observation. Client and her mother were instructed to seek emergency care if signs or symptoms of an allergic reaction occur later this evening.

She did not receive any Epipen or Benadryl (is allergic to it) but wanted to take a box of Claritin 10 mg with her (said it always helps). SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt was admitted on 5/10/21 c/o of rigor.  Patient complains of fatigue, weakness, intermittent fevers up to 100.8 �F.  EMS found patient to be hypotensive up to 84/52 and tachycardic up to 120s per minute. He woke up the morning of admission and then began to have shaking rigors at 10 AM and felt profoundly fatigued, dizzy and lightheaded.  Patient does have a history of COPD which is non-O2 nonsteroid dependent and has some chronic shortness of breath.  He does use inhalers and nebulizers and also continues to smoke.  He also has a history of melanoma who follows with provider.  In the ER he was found to have hypotension and was given 2 L of IV fluids.  He also had a 3 g drop in his hemoglobin over the past 5 days and there was concern for a possible upper GI bleed.  Because of the hypotension and drop in hemoglobin he was admitted to the ICU.  He was started on Protonix IV.  Chest x-ray, CT of the chest CT of the abdomen and pelvis were unremarkable for any acute process.  He was admitted for unspecified shock which was initially thought possibly due to sepsis but this was ultimately ruled out.  He was treated with 5 days of vancomycin and Zosyn and then antibiotics were discontinued.  Patient's troponin was elevated with an elevated delta.  He was seen In consultation by cardiology who felt that no further cardiology work-up was needed the cause for the patient's hypotension was unclear but his home lisinopril was discontinued.  he did require albumin but not pressor support.  As he was more stable he was transferred out of the ICU to the medical floor.  He was started on midodrine.  His blood pressure has improved he has remained afebrile throughout his hospital course he has remained stable off antibiotics.  At this time he is medically stable for discharge to home and will continue on midodrine for new autonomic failure/dysfunction. the cause for his fevers/rigors was not found

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received the 1st COVID vaccine (Pfizer, lot #EW0185, use by 05/23/21, expiration: 08/21) at 1411. Client notified EMT that she was feeling nauseous EMT immediately helped the patient to the anti-gravity chair. The client vomited a small amount of vomit, no blood was in the vomit and it was a light green color. The client reported eating avocado and a quesadilla prior to being vaccinated around noon. RN assessed the client who was alert and oriented to person, place, time, and situation.  The patient was offered juice and water, denied experiencing this reaction in the past with other vaccines. Vital signs were taken at 1422, BP- 125/86 (Right arm, sitting upright), HR- 82, RR- 16, oxygen saturation- 97%. The client denied experiencing a similar reaction with other vaccines in the past. Client reported, " This is what I was like when I had Covid-19 months ago, I was just really nauseous." Denied shortness of breath, chest pain, vision changes, or difficulty swallowing. The client stated, " My nausea is a lot better, I'm feeling better." Vital signs were taken at 1434, BP- 136/86 (Right arm, sitting upright), HR- 75, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 97%. Client continued to deny shortness of breath, lightheadedness, chest pain, blurred vision, or changes in vision. At 1453 the patient had another episode of vomiting, it was a small, green amount of emesis, no blood or mucous was present. The patient was given 50mg diphenhydramine at 1457 and denied Emergency Medical Services. RN educated the patient about emergency room precautions and advised the client to follow-up with her primary care provider. Vital signs were taken at 1455: BP- 140/86 (Right arm, sitting upright), HR-68, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 100%. The client was educated about diphenhydramine and that it may cause drowsiness, so the client called her brothers to pick her and her daughter up. The patient continued to report feeling nauseous, and then stated," I feel like I'm getting back to normal." Vital signs were taken at 1508, BP- 140/ 82( Right arm, sitting upright), HR- 60, RR-16, oxygen saturation- 99%. The client continued to report, " I feel like I'm getting back to normal." Vital signs were taken at 1513, BP- 136/82 (Left arm, sitting upright), HR-70, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 98%. Client denied difficulty breathing, shortness of breath, difficulty swallowing, or wheezing. The client dry- heaved and had a scant amount of green phlegm present, no blood was observed. Vital signs were taken at 1518, BP- 138/82 (Left arm, sitting upright), HR- 82, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 97%. The client reported feeling less nauseous. Vital signs were retaken at 1523, BP- 132/82 (Left arm, sitting upright), HR- 74, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 97%. Vital signs were taken at 1528, BP- 132/82 (left arm, sitting upright), HR- 63, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 97%. Vital signs were retaken at 1533, BP- 128/80 (Right arm, sitting upright), HR- 70, RR-16, oxygen saturation at 99%. RN educated the client about V-safe and gave her a handout on it, in addition to reiterating the importance of following up with the clients primary care provider, educated the client about emergency room precautions, and the importance of preventing dehydration by intaking an adequate amount of fluids and electrolytes. The client was waiting for her brothers to arrived on site, as she felt a little drowsy from the diphenhydramine. At 1552, the patient dry-heaved and had a scant amount of phlegm present, no blood present. The patient was given another emesis bag and vital signs were taken at 1554, BP- 130/ 80 (right arm, sitting upright), HR- 85, RR-16, oxygen saturation 100%. The client's brothers arrived on site at 1554, RN gave report to the brothers, educated them about following up with the primary care provider, emergency room precautions, and the importance of being adequately hydrated. The client stated, " It just comes and goes but I don't feel as nauseous right now." At 1600, the client ambulated to the car with a steady and even gait.

I went for a new covid test 4 days later and it was negative. Around day  22 - 25   my headaches finally stopped, I started being able to catch my breath more and was getting more energy. Client received her 2nd Moderna shot (Lot# 024C21A) at 15:40 and client's mother was accompanying her.  After receiving the shot, client went to observation room to sit in a chair.  At 15:45 EMT noticed client feeling drowsy.  EMT approached client and her mother.  Client stated she felt like she was going to pass out.  Mother helped client stay upright in chair while EMT grabbed recliner chair.  EMT transferred client to recliner chair and notified Lead RNs over waki taki.  EMT took client's vitals at 15:50 (BP:  122/82, HR:  78) and gave client a bottle of water.  Lead RN arrived in observation room at 15:52. EMT communicated that client was clammy, diaphoretic and nauseous.  Client stated she was already feeling better and that the symptoms only lasted 2 minutes.  Client stated she was not experiencing SOB or difficulty breathing.  Client was alert and oriented times 4.  Client also stated she experienced the same exact symptoms after her 1st dose of Moderna.  Client stated she feels like she is going to pass out when she gets shots, but that it passes quickly.  Client stated she has no underlying conditions, takes no medications, and has no known allergies.  Client also stated she did not take any medication or receive treatment for these symptoms after receiving her 1st Moderna dose.  Client stated she ate and drank plenty prior to getting her 1st and 2nd shot and was feeling completely fine.  Client sat up in the recliner chair and sat for a bit longer.  EMT took vitals again at 16:14 (BP:  132/96 HR:  82, RR:  16).  Client stood up from chair and felt fine.  Client left with mother at 16:18. Client walked upright with a steady gait when leaving.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approx 27hrs after 2nd dose I felt my heart suddenly started irregular beats, arrhythmia with dizzy feeling, flush on face which lasted a minute or 2 followed by very rapid / hard beating of my heart (I could see my shirt move on my chest from the beating). This lasted for almost 10 minutes. Very scary. Paramedics were called about 5 minutes into the episode.  (I had a similar reaction of dizzy, flush with rapid and hard heart beat reaction after 1st dose about 5 minutes after it was given which lasted couple minutes then subsided).  When the paramedics arrived, I was laying down in my bed trying to relax and breath. By then the rapid and very hard beating of heart was calming down but was still elevated pulse for a resting position...~128bpm.  My BP was measured at 154/87.  They connected the 12point electrodes and the reading came back normal...only elevated pulse.  Paramedics ran 3 more scans during the  20 minutes they were there for...all came back normal.  My O2 was 100%. I elected to no go to ER since we live only 2 miles from the local hospital and I was feeling much better by then...but would go if I had another heart episode.  I have had none since.  Only other strange side effects was sore arm for 2 day and I notice is constant ringing in my ears all the time...strange.  I hope that will go away soon...very annoying.
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer 1st dose COVID vaccine

Weird reactions and increase in seizures with movement of any kind (in wheelchair, in car, carrying her from chair to bed, etc). Never had this before. Looked odd in her face, glassy eyes for a few days, weird movements. Her doctor called it a cytokoline storm type reaction at first but then she never went back down to her baseline for her seizures as they kept getting worse and worse. Finally on March 24th we did a medication infusion via IV to try to break the cycle and then on April 1st we started her on another seizure medication. On April 28 we increased the new seizure medication trying to get her back down to her baseline. She has never gone back down to her baseline, she is still dealing with an increase in seizures. She has days where she is just seizing all day long off and on for no other reason. Her team of doctors and I are 110% (yes 110%) sure this is a reaction to the vaccine. They called off the second dose, considered J&J vaccine but then with the risk of clots and her not 100% stable due to the first vaccine reaction we decided to hold off. This is horrible because for the last year I lived for the day to get her vaccinated to be protected from COVID and now she can't be. I am devastated and so afraid for her life because as you see in her dx she is very high risk for COVID death. We love to travel and just started cruising as she loves it and now we can't because she isn't vaccinated. She can't go back to her life the way she knew it before the pandemic because of the vaccine not being safe for her. :(

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 2021.05.20, 11:30PM felt unusually tired after my daily evening 3-mile walk. Muscles all over my body ached. 2021.05.20 12 midnight - 2021.05.21 8:00AM - slept very poorly with several interruptions, lots of sweating, mattress and bedding damp by the morning. I did not feel hot like when I have a fever. 2021.05.21 - 8:00AM - 9:00PM - Felt weak and lethargic. Muscle pain all over body continued. I needed to nap for two hours during the day. My heart rate was elevated about 15 percent above normal. After the nap I still felt tired. Food helped a little, but I went to be early, at 9PM. 2021.05.21 - 9:00PM - 2021.05. 22 - 8:00AM - Slept poorly with several interruptions, chills, and night sweats. Again awoke with damp mattress and bedding. For the first 10 minutes after rising I felt a little better, but then the muscle pain intensified and the lethargy too. I spent several hours of the day lying down in bed. Ate normally, which improved my overall feeling and energy level. Also consumed electrolytes and water. In the evening I started to feel not fully recovered, but a lot better than 24 hours prior. I went to bed at 11PM. 2021.05.22 - 11PM - 2021.05.23 - 10AM - I had some chills on preparing my bed, but overall slept better. Some sweating still.  2021.05.23 10AM - present 8PM - Felt much better. 95 percent of normal.

24 hours later, had extreme dizziness, nausea, pins and needles all through my body a metal taste in the mouth for 3 weeks after the injection. Exactly a week later at 8:40 pm my left arm at the injection site grew a bump at the same time my left upper eyelid blew up. My arm later developed a red patch for three days. Currently my eyelid is still healing.
LAB_DATA: Went to the doctors 5 times within a 12 day period. They just wrote down my symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vaccine administered to a person under the age of 18

Observed pt. sitting in a wheel chair with mom and EMT.  Pt. awake, alert, verbal, complaining of feeling flush after taking 1st dose of Pfizer vaccine@12:43pm.  Vitals taken by site EMT.  Vitals within normal range.  BP 114/72, O2Sat 100%.  12:55 pt. stated, "I'm feeling better now."  Pt. observed by staff for 30 min. before leaving to go home.  1:20pm pt. left vaccine site to go home with mom with no signs of acute distress.  Patient and parent educated by staff about Pfizer vaccine.  Verbalized understanding.

The patient was tested for Herpes due to some ulcers in her vaginal area (vaginal ulceration) and the test was negative.  At the reporting time, the patient was fully recovered, and the symptoms pain, oedema genital, and vaginal ulceration lasted for one week.   The causal relationship between the events and the suspect vaccine was not provided.

At approximately 6 PM on 05/23/2021, family was sitting down for dinner when all of a sudden she noticed that he was turning his head to the left and appeared to be falling out of his chair.  Mom states that eyes were darting back and forth at this time.  He was not responding to her shouting his name and his left arm was curled in towards his body with the rest of his body remaining stiff.  This lasted approximately 1 minute, followed by a time of confusion and drowsiness.  Approximately 1 minute later mom states that patient's eyes rolled back to his head and he had full body movement consistent with tonic-clonic seizures.  Family were able to lay him onto the ground during this time.  Mom denies any color change, apnea, or loss of bowel or bladder.  States he did have one episode of emesis following the event, and 2 episodes of emesis in the ambulance on the way to ED.  Patient has no previous history of seizures or seizure-like activity.  No new ingestions.  Has not been sick recently and denies any new sick contacts.  There has been no head trauma.   Per Mom, patient's dad has a history of "partial seizures" but never required any medication for them.   At arrival to the ED he continued to be drowsy and not at his normal baseline.  Continue to hold his left wrist up toward his body in a contracted manner and tended to have repetitive speech.   Briefly, ER course significant for a CT head and evaluation by pediatric neurology.  CT head was unremarkable for acute intracranial process.  A CBC, CMP, and coags were also obtained due to patient's continued contracture positioning and the possibility of a stroke.  CMP was unremarkable with a sodium of 139, potassium of 3.7, chloride of 107, bicarb 25, BUN of 12 and creatinine of 0.64.  CBC was also unremarkable with WBC of 10.72, hemoglobin of 14.8, hematocrit of 44.4 and platelets of 370.  There was 81.77% neutrophils after evaluation by neurology it was felt that the patient remained postictal and recommended that he be admitted on continuous EEG and possible MRI in the a.m.

24 hours after the second Moderna dose, I began to feel very weak with a strong headache and a low grade fever. By Thursday (48 hours after vaccination) the headache was very strong and by that night it was debilitating. The fever had increased as well to between 101-102 degrees. Thursday night Friday I treated symptoms with alternating doses of Ibuprofen and Acetaminophen, which succeeded in reducing the fever but did not rid of the headache. Saturday the debilitating headache persisted with extreme light sensitivity and nausea. The pain became so great Saturday night that my wife took me to the Emergency Room. There they performed a brain scan with an MRI that came back normal and treated the pain with Morphine. I was sent home around 8am Sunday morning with a prescription for Toradol. The pain did not decrease with the Toradol and by 6pm Sunday I was vomiting blood and the pain was excruciating. At the advice of my primary care doctor, I went back to the Emergency Room. In the Emergency department they performed a Lumbar Puncture and collected spinal fluid for testing, as well as blood for lab work. The pain was managed with Fentanyl. Late that evening the Hospital admitted me. I was given two more MRI's of the brain - one with contrast. I also underwent an upper scope of my esophagus, stomach, and upper colon which found 3 small ulcers likely due to the high volume of NSAID pain relievers taken over the previous days. The lumbar puncture revealed that my white blood cell count was 51 and they officially diagnosed aseptic meningitis.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: ?Brainstem Encephalitis?  Patient admitted to inpatient on 05/16/2021. Presented to the ED with dizziness, nausea, general fatigue and diplopia.  Patient also voiced an intermittent mild headache.  Patient was evaluated at an Urgent Care on 5/14/2021 with a ?presumed viral type illness?. In the ED, the patient denied neck pain, photophobia, eye pain, one sided weakness/numbness, facial droop, cough, congestion, and SOB.  Temperature max at home was 100.8F.  The patient does have gaze deficit and nystagmus on exam.  Negative toxicology screen. Negative SARS-COV-2 Antigen. ALT 86. Medical history includes: hypertension, depression, Vitamin D deficiency. Neurology- This is a 56-year-old patient referred to Neurology secondary to diplopia.  The patient states that her symptoms started with generalized fatigue and "not feeling well".  After 2 to 3 days [last Thursday 5/13/2021] she began having difficulty with double vision.  She has double vision in multiple directions.  The double vision is fairly constant.  Along with the double vision she feels off balance to the point where she has difficulty with walking.  She does admit to internal vertigo.  Patient denies any recent viral infections.  She is about 4 weeks out from her last COVID-19 vaccination which was Moderna.   During the hospitalization the patient has developed urinary retention requiring a foley catheter.  Hospital medications include IV Solu-medrol and subcutaneous heparin.  Patient seen by internal medicine, neurology, infectious disease, and urology during hospital stay.  The patient was discharged on 22MAY2021 after demonstrating ability to ambulate. Will continue with physical therapy outpatient.   See Tests and Lab Results Below
LAB_DATA: 05/16/2021- CT Head Without Contrast-a somewhat ill-defined rounded area of increased abnormal T2 and FLAIR signal centered within the midbrain, as best demonstrated on series 4 image 10 and series 2 image 14. No evidence of associated enhancement or significant restricted diffusion. Given patient's history and presenting symptoms, this is felt to most likely represent a focal area of encephalitis 5/16/2021-Chest XRAY- No evidence of acute cardiopulmonary disease 5/16/2021- CT Angiogram Head Neck with and Without Contrast- 1. There is no occlusion in the anterior or posterior circulation. The right anterior cerebral artery fills through the anterior communicating artery. The right posterior cerebral artery fills through the right posterior communicating artery. 2. Vertebral arteries are patent bilaterally. 3. Small calcified plaques at the origins of both internal carotid arteries but these are not flow limiting. 5/17/2021- MRI Brain With and Without Contrast- No acute intracranial abnormalities. Mild Chronic ischemic white matter changes. 5/17/2021- CT Abdomen Pelvis IV contrast only- No acute abnormality to explain symptoms. Trace bilateral effusions with dependent atelectasis. Tiny, circumscribed nodule in the medial right breast. Favor benign etiology.  5/17/2021- Fluroscopy Guided Lumbar Puncture- CSF WBC=285, clear, colorless. Otherwise negative. Oligoclonal Panel Completed-Profile Abnormal.  Oligocloncal Bands Negative, Serum IgG- 901, CSF IgG-9.8, Serum albumin- 4007, CSF Albumin-76, Isoelectric focusing revealed matching or identical oligoclonal bands in the CSF and the serum, result consistent with a systemic immune reaction.  5/19/2021- MRI Angiogram Head without Contrast- No evidence of intracranial arterial occlusion.  Tests for lyme disease/west nile virus negative.

The first shot, everything was fine. I had the normal side effects. The second shot I received on 05/08/2021, I felt fine afterwards, there were normal side effects. That following Monday 05/10/2021 I started to have pain in the labia minora, swelling in the vaginal canal, and general vaginal discomfort. I went to the doctor the following Monday (05/17/2021), my doctor told me I was having a HSV-2 (Herpes simplex) breakout. I had been diagnosed with HSV-2 four years before in November of 2017. This shocked me because I have not had a breakout since my initial breakout in November of 2017. I have taken 1 gram of  Valacyclovir every few days (2-3 times a week) for the last four years as recommend by my primary care doctor. I firmly believe that the second dose of the vaccine triggered something in my body that caused the herpes breakout. As of today (05/24/2021) it has not gone away. I look forward to more developing research and hopefully my testimonial will help collect data and information as the possible side effects of this vaccine. Thanks.  * I want to note I have NOT had ANY other side effects at all. *

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Existing tinnitus suddenly got very loud, louder than I have ever experienced it, and constant. It has never affected my quality of life. Twelve days after my first dose of Pfizer it is now a 7 or 8 out of 10 and is constant.  No fluctuation whatsoever.  It has now been like this for 12 days.  No relief.
LAB_DATA: Went to the ENT on 5/18/21.  Had a hearing test, which showed some high frequency hearing loss at the 4000 Hz range  (about the same level as when  I had been tested 10 years previously), some built-up ear wax, but no inflammation, no fluid in the ears.  The ENT and the audiologist both said they had seen a lot of people recently coming in complaining about new onset tinnitus or worsening tinnitus after the vaccine.   Otoscopy: clear AU;  Tymps: normal AU; AD: mild to moderate SNHL at 3k-8kHz; AS: moderate SNHL at 4k-8kHz; Excellent WRS aU; hearing essentially stable.
HISTORY: Existing very low-level tinnitus for the past ten years.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She got her vaccine, she told her about the medicine that she had anaphylaxis too, she asked if she had any lip fillers.  She waited the 15 minutes and then left, then started with a really bad headache and nausea, which she was fine before that.  On the way home her husband wanted to stop and she said no as she was sick, made it home and started throwing up, very tired and went to bed which she never does but was extremely sick.  Had fever of 100.1.  She would go from sweating to fever, aches and pains, flu-like symptoms, everything hurt, pain in the arm, couldn't use her dominant arm but has lymphedema in the other arm due to having her breast removed due to cancer.   Her lips were hurting her and never has chapped lips and had a lot of pain in them.  Looked in the mirror on Friday as her lips were really hurting and found they were swollen and her eyes looked like somebody had punched her in them.  She called her doctor and they did not return her call.  She didn't feel it was anaphylaxis as she did not have any other symptoms.  She put ice on her lips, had take a Zyrtec before the vaccine, but did use the Nasacort and couldn't figure out was going on.   She had not used anything new on her lips or anything.  Was thinking she had partial anaphylaxis.  Went online and saw the reactions as they did not give her a list of them.  She called her doctor and they told her to go to the ER.  She still has some swelling and redness with pain, but not an emergency for her to go to the ER.  Her lips are swollen, very tiny flat things in her mouth.  Wants to know if she's OK to get 2nd vaccine as her PCP will not call her back.

She looked woozy, with her eyes closing, and the nurses laid her down on the floor on a mat.  Her tongue and throat began swelling, and she was having extreme difficulty breathing.  She then could not feel anything from her neck down, like she was paralyzed.  The nurse administered an Epipen and EMS showed up minutes later.  In the ambulance, EMS administered another Epipen, gave her a steroid and Benadryl and rushed her to the hospital.  Once at the ER, she was still having a hard time breathing, and could not feel anything from the waist down and could not move her legs.  She also complained about her spine being in extreme pain around the mid to lower back.  When her symptoms did not resolve, she was admitted to the hospital for observation and treatment.  She had extreme pain in her joints - spine, hips, knees, ankles and toes, if someone tried to move them, she could not move on her own.  She also had tingling and numbness that would travel up and down her body - weakness in her arms and legs.  The medical staff continued with Bendryl - switched to Adderax, and Motrin and steroids (Prednisone?).  She was discharged from the hospital Sunday, 5/23/21 in the afternoon.  This morning (Monday 5/24/21) she is still experiencing back and leg pain, weakness and cannot walk with out assistance and it is extremely painful.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Dizziness - pharmacy technician did not give me the option to wait - it was not offered or recommended.  Immediately after the vaccination was given, I was free to go.  I had a few things to pick up in the store and as I was headed up the aisle to the checkout, I immediately became dizzy and had to hold on to the shelf to keep myself upright.  As I approached the counter, I noticed the pharmacy staff was heading out on break.  I stopped one of the reps and explained that I didn't feel well and asked if I should go and sit down until the dizziness subsided.  She replied yes and explained that they were on lunch but the pharmacist may come out.  As I head back to the rear of the store, I continued to feel dizzy.  The pharmacist was coming from the back (an office outside of the pharmacy) to accept a delivery and I explained that I was dizzy and was going to sit down.  He shook his head yes, but never came back to check on me.  I waited approximately 20 -25 minutes then left the store.  *After talking with relatives and friends, all of them were required to wait at least 15 minutes before becoming mobile.  Perhaps this option wasn't given to me since it was close to the time when the pharmacy closes for lunch.  Later that day, my left leg began to hurt near my calf and it was extremely difficult for me to walk.  I googled the side-effects and read that muscle cramps were possible, so I did not seek further medical attention.  The pain was intense but had resolved by Saturday morning.

Employee came to   for 2nd COVID19 vaccine dose.  The MA drew up a full vial that was not diluted. Therefore, the employee received more vaccine than he should have.  Once discovered, the employee was contacted by the  Medical Director, was told about the incident and what to expect, and was instructed to call   or the medical director with any concerns.  Pharmacy were notified. administrative oversight for  were also notified. The vaccine vial had been sitting in an opaque bag on the counter as it needed to be at room temperature for 15 minutes before reconstitution. The vial (lot number EW0179) was intact and no expiration sticker was on it.  Since this event, the clinic has changed practice of drawing up each dose as needed and will draw up all 6 doses from a vial, label/date them, and place in an opaque bag ready for use.  The syringes will be good for 6 hours as verified with pharmacy.  The  clinic administers many vaccines, all of which are unit dose.  Drawing up all syringes from a COVID19 vial will more closely align with this practice.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 4-18-21, 17 days after 1st dose of Moderna, he developed upper abdomen pain, chest discomfort. He thought it was indigestion and treated it as such. When he got no relief he went to Emergency room where a cardiac alert was initiated. After he died I was told he had developed myocarditis,/pericarditis and they had to remove a liter of blood from the sac around his heart, but that his heart had gone into cardiogenic shock and that he died. They were prepared to insert a stint thinking he had a blocked coronary artery, but his arteries were clear and they had no idea what had caused this to happen.  When he died so soon after the vaccine there were people who wanted to blame the vaccine but I checked into it and there were NO links between the vaccine and myocarditis, pericarditis or cardiogenic shock.  Within a few weeks of his death, there began to be possible links between the vaccine and myocarditis. I know 55 is older than what is being looked at, but he had absolutely no previous cardiac history prior to this and this case should e looked at as well
LAB_DATA: Pericardiocentesis, many blood tests, medical records available upon request
OTHER_MEDS: Ibuprofen prn for back pain, tums very rarely

SYMPTOM_TEXT: During injection, felt pins and needles from injection site to fingertips which faded to tingling and stopped entirely after about 7 minutes.   Intense nausea and sweating beginning 1-2 minutes post injection; unable to sit up. Lasted approximately 7-10 minutes before clearing up  2 hours later (7:10 pm), arm at and above injection site felt hot to the touch and had mild dull pain at every movement. Slightly dizzy and nauseous. Arm periodically ached without movement.  By 7:26 pm, arm pain from movement was a sharp pain, though still pretty mild.  Around 9:30 pm, gently pressed at site of injection and a jolt of pain went all the way down to my fingers  Nausea increased at 10:13, still mild. Decided to go to sleep. Woke up at least 5 times before 12:30 am in various states of pain and discomfort, including nausea when attempting to sit up; dry throat/mouth; pins and needles throughout my glutes and thighs accompanied by pain in my left hip, knee, ankle, and jaw; and mild to moderate arm pain at the injection site. Took about 15 minutes to be able to get up due to nausea and got some water.  Was cold so wrapped myself in a blanket. Nausea and arm pain with movement remained but I was able to go back to sleep around 1:15 am.  Woke up at 2:53 am - arm pain minimal and nausea gone, blanket felt nice but unnecessary, went back to sleep  Woke up at 5:34 am with pins and needles  in glutes and thighs and pain in my right jaw, knee, hip, and ankle (all sites of previous moderate injuries) along with a low grade headache. Went back to sleep.  Woke up after an hour or so feeling relatively normal, arm pain and headache returned after sitting up. Got out of bed but ended up taking another nap.  Woke up after another hour with just a headache and brain feeling fuzzy, but strong tingles began returning to my glutes and thighs  like they had fallen asleep (referred after this point as tingles). Arm hurt. Drank some more water and took another nap.  Woke up around 9:15 am with a low grade headache and slight tingles; fuzzy brain feeling was gone. Legs wobbly when I walked. Realized that tingling got worse anytime I was sitting down or lying on my back.  Around 10:20 am started crying - no known cause. Couldn't stop for a few minutes. This is not normal for me.  Around 1 pm realized I had a pretty high fever; unsure how high it was or how long I'd had it. Took another nap at 1:30 pm and woke up at 2:20 pm feeling much less hot so I thought it had broken, but I was told by my friend who dropped by that I was still feverish just much lower.  Slept from about 2:45-3:55 pm; headache was much better when I awoke; tingles and sore arm remained.  Realized at 4:13 pm that I'd had no appetite the whole day. I'd also barely been able to force myself to drink water; too cold and it hurt, room temperature didn't feel right.  No times, but felt periodic stabbing pain in my left ear until about 6:30 pm.  Much else also recovered by 6:30 pm: felt well enough to drink cold stuff, tingles were low grade, fever was present but low. Arm was still sore.  7:08 pm headache was gone.  8:49 pm felt much better and able to do things and take care of myself with minimal discomfort, but felt a little lousy overall - low grade headache, head felt like there was some pressure in it, periodic tingles, achy arm.  9:29 pm felt exhausted and slightly achy but otherwise mostly normal. Felt some hunger twinges for the first time that day but nothing felt appealing (realized I had only eaten about 5 spoonfuls of soup the whole day). Fell asleep getting ready for bed; woke up at 10:49 pm and finished getting ready for bed then went back to sleep.  Summary: Friday: Symptoms: mild to moderate nausea, mild dizziness, mild to moderate injection site pain, pins and needles in glutes and thighs, joint pain  Treatment: drinking water  Saturday:  Symptoms: mild to moderate pain at injection site, headache, fever, nausea, tiredness, glute and thigh tingles, lack of appetite, periodic stabbing pain in left ear  Treatments: ice/cold pack on arm (helped with arm pain while on), drinking water, sleeping

The report from my ECG states the results were abnormal. I had normal sinus rhythm and low voltage QRS; and they could not rule out anterior infarct. A urinalysis also suggested I had a UTI, and they prescribed me Macrobid. A follow-up analysis on 05/07/2021 suggested no infection. I have never had a UTI or any heart problems and believe these are all adverse effects of receiving the Pfizer vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initially I had experienced the standard adverse effects of drowsiness, a little difficulty sleeping, minor chills. The next day following my Dose 1 of the Moderna Vaccine, I started noticed chest pains on both sides of the chest. It wasn't from breathing and not very consistent or something I could re-create on command. It seemed to happen every hour for a few seconds and was a sudden, sharp pain. That was a concern for me so I did some basic internet searches and found that Chest pains are a symptom of the vaccine. I didn't think too much of it after that but It was a concern I kept in my head. My timeline gets a little foggy here but either that same day or the following day, the chest pains were still happening and I wasn't feeling 100%. One evening I went to take a bath. As I was laying in the water, my heart rate felt off, almost as if it was skipping a beat or not in the right rhythm. I remember laying in the bathtub, trying to count my pulse or seeing if I could "catch" the incorrect beat.  Rather than one normal heartbeat it felt like there was 2 beats very closely timed with each other. My heart rate felt faster than normal considering I was only laying down in water and didn't do any exercises the past few days. Unfortunately I never was able to find a good way to track the pulse and timing, but I was sure that something was wrong. I had difficulty sleeping that night because I kept feeling something wrong with my heart rhythm.  I got worried that I would need to go to the emergency room, but I told myself to sleep it off and if the chest pains and awkward heart beat continues for 5 days, I would go see a doctor. As for an outcome, thankfully I stopped noticing it around day 4 and haven't had chest pains since.  I am extremely worried as to how my body will react to Dose #2.
LAB_DATA: I did not take any lab tests related to the adverse effects since they subsided after a ~5 days days.

Blood clot in superficial vein behind right knee as well as vertigo and nausea.  Currently on 30mg/day of XARELTO blood thinner (I've been taking since diagnosis on 5/5/21).  Will continue to take 20mg/day for the next 30 days.  Background: I started to notice my right calf get tight and sore approximately ~3 weeks following my vaccination.  I had been doing a lot of running and hill training so I assumed it was a muscle strain/aggravation.  After approximately 1-2 weeks I noticed the tightness worsen and also noticed significant swelling around my lower calf/ankle.  I went to the doctor on 5/4/21 and was given a D Dimer blood test which came back 1.27 mcg/mL FEU (over the recommended 0.5 mcg/mL).  The next day I had an ultrasound of my right leg where they discovered the SVT clot behind my right knee in a superficial vein (but near a major/deep vein intersection).  I was immediately prescribed XARELTO blood thinner - to be taken for ~51 days.  ~21 days of 30mg/day (15mg twice/day) followed by ~30 days of 20mg/day 1x per day.  The morning of 5/20/21 around 6:30am I started to feel nausea and vertigo after returning home from walking my dog.  I finished a low-intensity exercise routine at my home and around ~7:15am my symptoms worsened.  I went upstairs to my bedroom to lay down on my bed and the room started spinning.  I then went to the bathroom and vomited clear fluid.  I started feeling a little better after vomiting but was still slightly dizzy and light-headed.  I made an appointment and went to the doctor around 10:30am.  The doctor suggested doing further bloodwork and a CT scan of my head.  Both tests came back normal.  The doctor suggested the vertigo and nausea were inner ear related and that I should continue taking XARELTO and to also start wearing a compression sock (especially during exercise/activity).

When I woke up on 1/29/21 at about 9 AM, I had a migraine that was especially painful behind the left eye. Then I had numbness and tingling on the left side of the face, with swelling and a slight droop on the left side of my face, from the eyebrow, to the cheek and downwards.  I also had spinal pain. I endured this for the next 3 days. On 1/31/2021, the drooping and swelling went away in the morning. I took ibuprofen and Tylenol, and the migraine went away on the 1/31 at between 6 and 8 PM. The spinal pain vanished at about the same time as the migraine. I called my doctor on 1/29, and I was told to go to the ER if the symptoms became unbearable. I never went to the ER, though. I just intermittently took Tylenol and ibuprofen to manage the pain between 1/28 and 1/31. When I went to get the second vaccine, the nurses refused on account of my previous experiences, because they didn't want to risk my becoming paralyzed. The nurses told me that if I received a release from my doctor, I could get the second injection at the hospital under my doctor's care. My doctor told me that if the nurses had concerns about paralysis, she could not authorize a second injection.

The pt was was responding and A&Ox4. His initial vitals were 96/49, 42bpm, 96% on RA. The pt remained alert and said that he was trying to sit down in his chair, and then found himself on the ground. He had recently walked over from getting his Pfizer covid vaccine. He was unsure he if he had LOC or hit his head. The pt said he felt "a little dizzy," but he denied any pain, including head, neck, back, and chest. He denied feeling SOB. The pt was able to sit up with minimal assistance, and then was able to get himself on to a cot that was placed next to him. He vitals were checked and can be found below. He continued to remain alert and respond appropriately. He said he "felt better." EMS was called due to the pt's dizziness, 61/40 BP, and 31 bpm pulse. AMR and a fire crew arrived at 1131, placed the pt on their gurney and monitoring equipment, and brought the pt in to the ambulance. Approximately 5 minutes after shot was administered into my left upper arm, as I sat down to wait my 15 minutes as required, I started to feel a racing heart, lightheaded, shaky, nauseous and strange sensation in my body.  I was with my mother and my husband.  My husband noticed I was struggling and called over the paramedic on staff.  He came over and asked me questions, as to what I was feeling, he brought over a bottle water and asked if I wanted some Cola for the nausea, apparently it helps with nausea.  At first I didn't want it, then  I ended up taking a few sips.  The entire episode lasted approximately 30-35 minutes, and I felt my heartrate returning to normal, however, I continued to feel out of sorts, shaky.  Upon returning home, the entire evening of the day in question, I felt a heaviness in my head, ache over my eyes, then my body continued to feel strange, I was very tired, and of course, my arm began aching, I barely slept through the night, feeling strange sensations in my body, aching arm, and headache, nauseated.  I had taken Tylenol  after getting home from the vaccine shot.  I finally got what I remember, maybe 2 hours of sleep, waking up to go to the bathroom, and my legs felt like cement! I could barely walk! Pain was radiating up the back of my legs, thighs, and buttocks.  I held myself along the wall to the bathroom and could barely bend.  After using the bathroom, I once again felt a tremendous heaviness, cement-like legs, barely making it back to the bed.  Throughout the entire day I could barely walk, severe muscle spasms lower back, thighs stiffness, down the back of legs, severe pain.  I contacted my doctor, told him of what was happening and he stated not to go back for the 2nd shot due to my issues with the 1st.  This has been ongoing since April 28, 2021, today is May 24, 2021 almost one month later and I am no better.  Although I have had Fibromyalgia for several years and Chronic Fatigue Syndrome, since the vaccine, it has triggered a complete relapse of my condition, making it unbearable, painful.  I have been living on pain meds, and icing/heating on and off.  Now requiring physical therapy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received her first dose of the Covid vaccine without a problem. She was reading a magazine in a chair while waiting for me (her mother) to have the second dose in the same room. About 5 to 10 minutes has passed since patient had received her injection. I looked over at patient, her eyes had rolled back and she had slumped in her chair. I ran over to her - her face was very red and she did not appear to be breathing. Her eyes were open but were not focused. I sat her up as straight as I could while the technician who administered the vaccine ran for the pharmacist. This took a few minutes. By the time the pharmacist arrived patient was gaining consciousness but began throwing up (although mainly dry retching). Her face had gone pale. The pharmacist was very helpful - she gave patient some Coke to drink and took her blood pressure, which was low. After 30 minutes of observation we were allowed to leave. The event was very frightening. Patient was very pale for the rest of the day. She had a severe pain in her left arm (and leg) which gradually improved over the next three days. We are very worried about her taking the second dose of the vaccine.
Inflammation of eustachian tube

After the 15 minute waiting period, I felt fine. I did my grocery shopping while I was at the store, went home and worked the rest of the day at my desk. We ran errands in the evening like normal. I hadn't really noticed because we were busy, but my heart rate had been steadily increasing all afternoon and into the evening. My watch tracks my pulse rate and reports on screen. After I took a shower at 9:30, I noticed that my pulse felt high. I laid down, thinking it was just from taking a hot shower and it would go back down to normal.  That's when I looked at my watch report and it looked like a stair step, with my heart rate increasing steadily every few hours, starting at 4 p.m. It was currently 110-120 (my normal RHR is 60, and drops into the 50s when I'm asleep). I went to bed, hoping I was just in my own head about this and it would be fine. I woke at 2 a.m.  and my heart rate had not dropped below 100 while I was asleep and was at 130. I went to the ER at 2:00 a.m. because it was alarming. There were points where it spiked to 150 while sitting still. The ER ran an EKG, full blood and urine labs, monitored my heart rate and BP - my BP was in the normal range the whole time. The doctor who saw me in the ER was awesome. Her husband is still dealing with lingering neurological damage from having COVID last year. She informed me that I was not in a-fib or any type of cardiac distress and my labs were all normal, but was likely having an immune response to the vaccine.  They did a chest x-ray and CT to check for blood clots and both came back negative. My platelet count was well within normal range as well. I returned home about 6 a.m.  and my heart rate was still higher than normal, but had already started to work its way down. It stair-stepped down just like it went up and by 4 p.m., my RHR was back down to 70 and it was down in the 50s overnight. Aside from that, I had the typical headache, low-grade temp and overall body aches. Everything had subsided by Sunday afternoon. I did make an appointment see my PCP as instructed by the ER doctor on Tuesday, April 13. She had read all reports from the ER and was pleased with how my heart rate had come back down to normal. This was the same day that the authorities stopped use of the Jannsen shot due to the blood clot concerns. Dr ran another platelet count for my own peace of mind and it was a little higher than it was when I was in the ER, so she was confident that I was not in any danger, but did review the symptoms/warning signs of blood clots with me just in case.  I have not had any issues or symptoms since.

OTHER_MEDS: Losartan, Smarty Pants Women's Multi-Vitamin, Smarty Pants Probiotic, Kirkland Calcium + D gummies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 1:30pm on Tuesday April 6th, I was sitting at my desk in my home office, working. I began experiencing moderate chest pain and shortness of breath. These symptoms continued to worsen for the next hour. I had difficulty breathing, and taking a full breath was painful enough to prevent me from doing so. I drove myself to the ER. While waiting in the ER, I began experiencing chills, severe joint pain, and moderate pain generally throughout my body beginning around 4:00pm, which I advised ER staff. While being examined by the ER doctor around 7pm, there was some tenderness noted in my right upper quadrant. My blood pressure was extremely high (205/130) and I developed an intense headache. I was admitted overnight and discharged the afternoon of April 7th. While the chills and pain improved on April 7th, my chest pain and shortness of breath continued for another week or so. The night of April 7th at home, I woke up several times with difficulty breathing and ended up sleeping fitfully while propped up at a 45 degree angle so I could at least breathe mostly normally. The chest pain and difficulty breathing slowly improved over about 10 days until I was no longer experiencing symptoms.
LAB_DATA: April 6, 2021: EKG 12-lead, troponin, CBC, CMP, Chest x-ray, lipase, d-dimer, blood glucose, CT chest w contrast, CT head without contrast, urinalysis, limited ultrasound of the abdomen  April 7, 2021: abdominal ultrasound, RSV, influenza, Covid-19

I changed out of jeans and then saw my legs had developed rashes in large sections; some looked like hives, some like little red bumps, some with just read splotches. I washed my legs thinking maybe a bug or allergen and put anti itch cream on one leg to see if it would help or if I needed anything else. I went to bed shortly after and then woke at 6am (Weds. May 19) and when I changed out of pj's, noticed rashes also at the injection site; the itching continued to come and go and when it would begin to itch, the rash/bumps would appear without scratching. The rashes would continue on primarily the legs and glutes but also injection side and a little on the shoulder/back of the same side of the injection site and small rash on each ear. I did not take any medication or apply any more anti itch cream despite the intense itching sensation.   I took pictures for documentation if you need them.

When I received the first dose 4/7/21, I had a burning sensation go up my left arm to my face.  My face felt hot and then my chest.  I felt scared like I could be having something wrong but I continued on.  I then got very tired.  The next day I felt achy knees. Two days later I started having buzzing in my ears but didn't realize it could be a side effect.  I went to a Urgent Care and was treated for a possible ear infection and given antibiotics.  That did not help or cure my condition.  The buzzing/ringing is on the same side/left as my injection.  On 5/5/21, I went for my second injection and asked if the buzzing/ringing or being on antibiotics was a problem, they said no.  The buzzing/ringing increased.  I went to my regular Primary Care doctor who didn't see anything  wrong.  She referred me to an ENT.  The ENT ran a hearing test.  The hearing test seemed to come back ok but I still have the Tinnitus.  The Tinnitus is worse at night and in the morning when everything is very quiet.  Some days are worse than others and I have seen no improvement.  I also am experiencing hot flashes.  They also happened after the first shot and increased after the second.  The Tinnitus is very bad at time and I want it to go away.  It is like buzzing in my left ear that is always there but sometimes I can tune it out.  I think it is important to report this as I have not had anyone tell me it is a possible side effect.  If it is than this needs to really be investigated and studied and communicated with people.  It is very disturbing as I have never had Tinnitus before.  I hope and pray it goes away and there are no other side effects.

1/24/21 I received the Moderna 1st vaccine through the county fairgrounds.  2/11/21 I started experiencing terrible mouth pain on the right side. This included pain in the bone, teeth, gums, cheek and right ear. Thinking it might be a bad tooth I went to the dentist the next day 2/12/21 Dr. took x-rays of the upper and lower right side and found no tooth problem 2/15 After taking continuing pain meds the pain in the right side of my mouth went away, but feeling fatigued.  3/2/21 I received the Moderna 2nd vaccine at the county fairgrounds. I was sick for 3 days with a low temperature. 3/10/21 I had my teeth cleaned and xrays at Dr. office Dental practice. He said everything looked good including fillings.  3/25/21 I started experiencing terrible mouth pain on the left side of my mouth. This included pain in the bone teeth, gums, cheek, right ear and right side of my throat.  3/26/21 I went to the Urgent care. Doctor could find nothing wrong. The Dr. prescribed 3 days of steroids. After 3 days of steroids and other pain meds the pain went away. 3/30/21 I was now experiencing tooth pain specific to the upper right back molar and the upper left back molar. They both felt loose ad pain when chewing. 4/7/21 I went to my dentist and he said the upper right molar appeared to be cracked and needed to be extracted. The upper left molar looked like it could be capped but then he found out later it was also cracked and had to be removed. 4/13/21 I was experiencing headache, fatigue, and shortness of breath when exerting myself. Talked to the triage nurse and made an appointment for 4/19/21 4/14/21 Upper right back molar cracked and was extracted by my Dr at the dentist. 4/19/21 Upper left back molar cracked and was extracted by my Dr at the dentist.  4/19/21 I saw a Dr at urgent care for fatigue, shortness of breath and headache. She did a checkup and blood work. 4/20/21 I was rushed to the emergency room for critically low hemoglobin (5.5) and given 2 units of blood, fluids, and a B12 infusion. 4/21/21 Endoscope procedure while in the hospital showed a possible hernia problem but there was no strong conclusive reason for my mouth pain, cracked teeth and low hemoglobin. I am now taking supplements and seemed much recovered. I believe this was a onetime event caused by the vaccine. My primary doctor, agrees the mouth pain has been reported as a side effect. In October of 2020 I had a complete checkup with my primary Dr.  and was found to be very healthy and did not have any problems until I received the vaccine. I would like to know if there is a pool of money I could draw from as I now need two implants to replace the two cracked teeth.

When Observation Staff  was releasing patient, patient reported not feeling well some itching on her neck, asked her if she could walk to the tent, she replied yes. She grabbed her belongings and walked to the tent, sat in the chair without assistance. I asked if she preferred to lay down on the cot, she replied, ?yes, that is probably a good idea?.  She complained of itching on her neck, hands bilaterally, and lower leg bilaterally for the last 5 minutes that ?feels like a bad sunburn?. She reported this is has happened before, several times, and is seeing a ?Functional Medicine Doctor? for the past 2 months to try and diagnose this condition. She mentioned the functional medicine doctor recommended she receive the COVID-19 vaccine.  She also began to feel a headache, dizzy ?but not because my head is spinning but because the ground is unstable?. No visual rash present on areas reported as itchy. She reported a history of low blood pressure, SVT, mitral valve regurgitation, hives, and Lyme disease. She mentioned her dad drove her here and is waiting in the parking lot. Reported she does not take any prescription medication only takes vitamin C, Zinc, a probiotic, and Claritin as needed for the itching. She mentioned she had some blood work done recently due to hormonal imbalance, digestive discomfort, and her history of Lyme disease.  Orthostatic laying: BP 105/64, HR 90 SPO2 99, BPM 19, 4/10 pain with the burning sensation Sitting: BP 105/62, HR 90 SPO2 99, BPM 18 Standing: BP 117/64, HR 90 SPO2 99, BPM 18 able to stand with out feeling dizzy or lightheaded for 5 minutes Took vital signs and chatted with the patient about her symptoms and she reported this reaction is similar to what she has been feeling in the past and why she is seeing her Functional Medicine Doctor. She had not taken Benadryl for this reaction recently and said it made her feel ?really drowsy? and does not remember it helping much. She brought Claritin 10 mg and took it since it what her fictional medicine doctor recommended.   Since her vital signs were WNL, she denied feeling worse, history of similar symptoms and events, patient was escorted out in a wheelchair for safety. She said she felt like she could walk on her own but agreed to be escorted out in the wheelchair. Wheeled out by PHN, patient was able to get out of wheelchair and into the SUV without assistance.
HISTORY: SVT, mitral valve regurgitation, low blood pressure, Lyme disease

The patient received his 2nd COVID-19 Pfizer vaccine on Thursday, 05/20/2021 in his left arm.  The patient developed a temperature of a 102.5� with aches, chill, and pain overnight.  The symptoms subsequently dissipated.  Around noon on 5/22 he began to experience an achiness and pressure beneath the sternum and it has been constant since.  The pain does not radiate into the back.  No associated ripping or tearing sensation.  No shortness of breath or difficulty breathing. In ED, EKG showed normal intervals, no ST changes and no STEMI. I was severely dizzy and lightheaded so I went back to bed until 6:30 am and the symptoms persisted so much and scared my husband enough to stay home from work to keep an eye on me. I slept so much that day and severely lightheaded dizzy and body numbness even on 1,000mg Tylenol. I am a highly sensitive person and a red head. I waited this long to get the shot because I know myself so well and wanted to see everyone else?s reaction. My husband got the Johnson and Johnson a week after mine and he was fine. No reaction. I called the cdc immediately after my reaction, I also had an odd swollen arm at injection site that wasn?t there for 10 days that appeared out of no where and it was super tender and painful and hot and itchy. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got my second vaccine on Friday January 15, 2021. On the following Monday (January 18), I started having chest pain around 5:00 pm before leaving work. The chest pain got worse until I woke up in the middle of the night afraid I was having a heart attack and vomiting. I got up and planned to go to the hospital at  around 5 am but the pain started to subside. I made an appointment to see my PCP the following Friday (January 22nd) and had cardiac labs drawn. My heart enzymes were elevated that day so my PCP chose to admit me into the hospital. I had a heart cath, wore a heart monitor, had EKGs, had my enzymes trended, and had a heart ultrasound. The cardiologist discharged me with possible myocarditis. I took a regimen of ibuprofen and symptoms subsided. I had been having chest pain off and on for about a month before this episode but thought it was heart burn because it was very mild.
LAB_DATA: I had a heart cath, wore a heart monitor, had EKGs, had my enzymes trended, and had a heart ultrasound. Everything was normal and my enzymes were normal when I left the hospital, but the cardiologist discharged me with possible myocarditis stating that it couldn't be "ruled out."

After about 5 minutes of administering the vaccine, the associate overlooking the observation area came to tell me a patient was not feeling well. I immediately grabbed my carat and went out to the IMZ area next to pharmacy. The patient was still seated and she was conscious, but appeared very weak, sweaty, and slightly pale and cold to the touch. I immediately made sure she could respond to my questions. She was able to respond. I asked if she had eaten before coming in and she confirmed she had not eaten that day yet.  I checked her blood pressure and it was 68/33. I stayed by her side and her mother was fanning her on the other side. I had her take several breaths in and out and could visually see her responses improving. She asked for water, which her father handed to her. I checked her blood pressure again and it was up to 125/68. She reported feeling much better and was able to joke around with her sister who also received the vaccine at the same time. I asked her to sit for an additional 15 minutes, on top of her original 30 minutes, and told her parents I would be back to check her blood pressure gain. I came back into the pharmacy and prepared another vaccine. After I administered the next vaccine, I checked her blood pressure again, which read 95/68 and her mom stated this was normal for her. I advised her to stand up slowly before walking. A few minutes later she came to the pharmacy window for her vaccine card and reported feeling normal and her parents thanked me and they all left.

He used to carry an epi pen but does not currently, also has a history of asthma for which he carries a rescue inhaler. He received the Pfizer vaccine at approximately 9:15am in his left deltoid, and about 2 minutes later Mom notified me and the school nurse that he was starting to get "hives". I noted a localized, small area of erythema on his left upper arm around the bandaid, approximately silver dollar sized, not raised. School RN removed the bandaid. He did not complain of itching and at that time stated he felt like he was breathing fine. The school RN gave him 50mg of Benadryl PO per the mom's request at 0920. The patient was in no distress, breathing and speaking normally. At 0922 he stated he felt like his throat and tongue were swelling, so I had him remove his mask, and asked mom if his lips looked swollen to which she responded "yes". He stated it felt like it was hard to swallow. We placed a pulse ox on the patient and his oxygen saturations were 96-100%, HR 85-90, RR 30. We administered an adult epi pen (0.3mg of epinephrine) into his left lateral thigh at 0923 and had the school office call EMS. The patient remained in no acute distress, and said the swelling in his tongue felt better after the epi, but that his throat still felt swollen. Lungs clear bilaterally, RR remained 24-30, HR 110-115, pulse ox 98-100%, erythema on left upper arm resolved. Fire department arrived at 0935- report given and they checked a pulse ox as well. Patient walked to parking lot to ambulance for transfer to Hospital with mother following behind.

1) Lots of pain during injection (more than ever experienced with another vaccine). 2) Pain subsided quickly after vaccination, and the typical sore arm feeling developed for the next 2-3 days. 3) After the sore arm feeling wore off, the vaccine injection site continued hurting slightly when pressure was applied, i.e. when laying on  my left arm. This symptom persisted for about 17 days. 4) On day 18, the injection site started hurting when moving my left arm, until I could not move my arm above my shoulder without pain. Pain was heavy during the night.  5) On day 20, my arm felt weak. I went to the primary care facility where I received the vaccine. A doctor diagnosed me with SIRVA (Shoulder Injury Related to Vaccine Administration), and subscribed me a two-week course of Ibuprofen (2x600mg per day). I am currently still on this course. Pain improved when taking Ibuprofen, but most days my arm still feels weak. Occasionally, the pain radiates through my arm towards my hand and on my back (left side).  It is not yet clear whether this injury will become permanent damage.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Adverse effects after 1st dose: Nothing happened until exactly 24-hours later. Then the next day, from 3:00pm to 11:00pm: bad chills, body aches, no headaches though, tiredness, low energy, feverish. Took 2 sets of 2 tylenols. After 11pm, everything cleared.  Adverse effects after 2nd dose: BAD!!! Injection was at 2pm, reactions started by 4pm. All of the effects from the 1st dose but almost doubled in intensity and lasted 2-3 days: feverish, tiredness, unable to move body, body aches, muscle aches, headaches. Unable to work during those days!!!   Then additional effects: VERY heavy, torrential period! 1st day of period was Tuesday, May 18, one day late.   Then: Herpes outbreak on the anus (first outbreak in a long time).    WORSE EVENT YET: Around May 18, my ear was itching. I naturally have ear fungus that has been easily treated over the years. But this one did not go away.  I tried to apply the cream, clean. Nothing. By Thursday, I felt an inflammation. By Friday afternoon, I could not hear much from the left year and the right year was starting to be itchy too. Went to a Urgent Care, the RNP prescribed a drop and told me to take Ibuprofen if needed. By 10pm that night, I was in excruating pain: fever, chills, body aches, muscle aches, the ear pain gotten really bad (never experienced this level before), unable to chew, gotten really cold (needed 5 blankets). Long night. By morning, I went to the walk-in clinic of my healthcare provider - VERY sick. The ear has gotten worse and the NP explained that the body was probably unable to fight the small infection in the year because body was still under the virus effect. With my science background, I am afraid that she's right and/or that the Moderna covid vaccine has suppressed my natural immune system!!! I had a really strong immune system prior to the vaccine, records will prove it. Got sent to ER. They never took me seriously when I said that this is ALL related to the vaccine!!! Got a CT Scan, luckily the infection did not make it to the brain. They prescribed an antiobiotics and let me go. Now, ear pain moved to the right. I can't hear.
CUR_ILL: Reactions to the 1st dose of Moderna Covid vaccine: headache, fever, chills, body aches, muscle aches, general fatigue for 2-3 days

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vaccine 3/15, 4/8. Admit 5/1. Admit for hypoxia d/t COVID PNA. H/O RA w/interstitial lung disease. In ER temp 100.1, SpO2 94%. WBC WNL, later elevated. CXR shows interstitial lung disease. Treated w/steroid, dose of convalescent plasma, supportive care, oxygen.   Brief History: Patient who presented with the above complaints.  Patient with a history of longstanding rheumatoid arthritis who presents to the ER with above-stated symptoms.  Patient reports history of chronic dry cough which she attributes to having lung disease related to rheumatoid arthritis.  Patient has received both doses of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, 2nd dose on April 8th.  About 2 weeks ago he started having low-grade fevers with worsening of cough and shortness of breath.  Patient was tested at an urgent care center and tested negative for COVID-19.  Denies any known sick contacts.  No recent travel history.  Symptoms worsened about a week ago with persistent fevers, increasing cough and shortness of breath.  Patient went to see his rheumatologist and diagnosed with interstitial lung disease this week and referred to see pulmonology.  He was monitoring his oxygen saturations at home which have been dropping down to 88-89% on room air that made him come to the ER.  Patient tested positive for COVID-19 in the emergency room.  CT angiogram of the chest showed no evidence of any pulmonary emboli but evidence of interstitial lung disease bilaterally.  He is currently being admitted for hypoxia secondary to COVID-19 pneumonia.  Patient denies any chest pain   Hospital Course:  Patient was admitted.  Kept on steroids and oxygen.  Seen by Infectious Disease.  Got a dose of convalescent plasma   This morning he is on room air.  Past the walk study.  Feeling lot better.  Seems to be stable for discharge on oral steroids to finish up the course.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The first symptom I experienced was a high grade fever that reached 103.5 degrees Fahrenheit. The fever lasted from 2:00pm on May 10th (the day it was administered) until 2:00 am on a May 11th (the early hours of the day after it was administered). Some weakness, as well as muscular soreness in the left arm persisted in the insuring days. The reason why I chose to report my experience is because something that I thought was abnormal happened. On the evening of May 15th, as I was putting on my pajamas, I noticed an irregular mass in my left breast. As I examined it further, I realized that this mass was not there previously and warning shots fired off in my head, immediately. I immediately asked my grandmother to do another examination of my breast, and she confirmed my suspicion that there was a foreign mass located above my nipple in my left breast. It was difficult for me to closely monitor this mass as it was difficult for me to think about it as it triggered emotional distress. I asked my mom to do an examination and she also noted the mass. A little more than a week later, I noticed that the mass shrunk. Since everyone in my family was on edge for nearly a week suspecting that a 21 year old female in their family could possibly have breast cancer, this caused my family to consult my grandmother?s doctor, and have her assistant contact me about what could potentially be happening. Her assistant spoke to me over the phone and communicated that it is important for me to have the mass formally examined and for me to receive a mammogram. She also mentioned that many women who have received the vaccine also noticed irregular lumps in their breasts after receiving the vaccine. I want women in my age range to be aware that they might notice lumps in their breasts after the vaccine and not to experience the same emotional distress of thinking that they have breast cancer when it could be inflammation occurring in their lymph nodes as a result of being administered the Covid vaccine.
LAB_DATA: I have yet to have an appointment with my doctor, but if asked, I will update the situation to those who request it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She got her vaccine, within 10-15 minutes she was talking to her sister and she put her hands out and she had not read any reactions.  She stretched out her arms in front of her and noticed that the middle fingers on the left hand was twitching. Then a little bit later there was a muscular contraction in the middle of her left thigh, midway between her hip and knee on the anterior side.  Was an intermittent muscular contraction on the same side she got the shot.  The twitching back and forth of her finger was 1/4 of he way.  She googled it and saw that it may be related to the vaccine.  Friday, it continued twitching back and forth like a metronome.  If she stretches her forearms out prone the ring finger, middle finger and especially the middle finger.  Saturday the symptoms were still there but not as much.   The thigh symptoms continued for about 2 hours.  She walked from her sisters house which is about 1/2 block and it disappeared.  The finger issues are more long-term and some numbness in the hand itself.  Her right hand at times this weekend had jiggling fingers, but the left is the worse.  It is intermittent movement and slight 1/8" movement on those 3 fingers still.  There is a general numbness in the fingers as well, not 100% like it's supposed to feel  This is going through the entire left arm and down into the hand.  It is not as constant that it was on Friday, getting better and just intermittent right now.  She has not contacted her doctor yet, but states that she will.   She noticed a clumsiness and a sense of unsteadiness with her walking and felt safe doing so.    She may have gotten COVD in Feb/March 2020, said she had almost every symptom from COVID and had lost her sense of smell, slight diarrhea, sore throat, runny dose, temp of 100.3.  She still has some loss of sense of taste.    She was told at one time that she had markers for Sjogren's.
PRIOR_VAX: She had a hepatitis B vaccine and got a bad rash on both shoulders.    Before that she had in the 1990's got a MMR and got sick

His fall was somewhat controlled by the technician. I then assessed the patient and determined he had a vasovagal episode and lifted his legs, he returned to consciousness within 10 seconds of raising his legs. I then allowed the patient to lie on the floor for approximately 20 minutes after which he felt better and returned to sitting . He then sat for about 15 more minutes until a family member was able to arrive. The patient reported no other adverse effects other than dizziness, lightheadedness, some trouble hearing and tingling fingers.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Covid-19 vaccine administrations (Moderna) 3/23/21 lot# 013A21A 4/20/21 lot# 013A21A  Admission to Hospital (5/2/21 ? 5/10/21) for hypertension and acute on chronic back pain requiring ICU admission, hyponatremia thought to be due to SIADH. CT of abdomen done at hospital noting no significant lumbar abnormalities and a plain film of her lumbar spine with no obvious compression fracture. Outside hospital notes do not further outline why she could no longer ambulate. Brain MRI done and negative during that admission. Discharged to a rehab facility for ongoing weakness.  On 5/13/21, patient?s son requested admission to hospital for further evaluation. She states that she feels confused and her legs are very heavy and she can barely move them.  Notably she lives alone in her own home, used to drive, did not use any assistive device to walk, and paid her own bills until 2 weeks ago. The symptoms did occur approximately a week after receiving her last Covid vaccine. Pt also notes around April 1, 2021 having taken an engorged deer tick off her head. 5/14/21 Lyme serology IgM & IgG = negative. Neurology was consulted. She had an MRI of her thoracic and lumbar spine, as well as an LP. She had had an MRI brain at a hospital. Her MRIs did not reveal a source of her weakness and pain. Her CSF revealed albuminocytologic dissociation. Given this finding and the constellation of symptoms and LP findings, it was thought she had Guillain Barre Syndrome, presumably due to her COVID vaccine. She was given IVIG for 5 days. She improved with this.    As above, she had a recent admission for hyponatremia and hypertensive urgency. Here, her blood pressure was somewhat labile, but at times was low. She was started back on amlodipine and carvedilol, but at much lower doses with plan for ongoing monitoring. In terms of her hyponatremia, her salt tabs were stopped, and eventually her fluid restriction was able to be lifted. Her sodium was 136 at discharge.
