SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 5 minutes, I felt soreness in my arm right away and my arm started throbbing. I got warm all over my body. My airway (not my throat or tonsils) in my chest area started to close and constrict. But it only went so far - it didn't finish closing. I got the sensation that I was going to faint. I was in my car. I yelled for help and went out of my car. I had no energy or ability to walk. I went down to ground and could barely lift my head up. I got very lethargic and was extremely tired and nauseous and I could hardly think. The person who gave me the injection and another lady who was helping out came to help me. My intuition told me I needed Benadryl and my hands were kind of moving to try to get Benadryl. But I could hardly get up. I wanted to call 9-1-1 but my toddler had my phone. I couldn't kneel up even to get my phone to from my toddler. I couldn't walk. They took my blood pressure and heart rate and noticed during the episode that they both had spiked. They said they couldn't give me Benadryl because then they told I wouldn't be able to drive. Then I had a second episode - where I started feeling like I was going to pass out again and a feeling of doom was coming over me and I think I asked for Benadryl again. I could barely hold up the pulse oximeter - I think I was dragging it on the ground; I was on the ground on the parking lot. I thought I was going to faint but I was able to finally get my phone and call my sister. My sister showed up and got dropped off. The ladies didn't help out at all and my sister was going to drive me away. My limbs were really cold and feet were really cold all the way to my knees. I asked for a heating pad. I couldn't get up for 30 minutes, and then for an hour. My tried to get better and I could barely stand up. It took me awhile to get into the car; my sister had to help me. The next day, I was still in the same predicament. I couldn't get up and walk around. After a really long time of resting, I could go a short distance to go to the bathroom alone. My sister (I was staying at her house since I couldn't take care of myself)  finally said that my intuition had told me to take Benadryl and she said I should take one. I took a half of child's of Benadryl because the people at the vaccine site had not thought I should have one and that it would just go away. That 1/2 dose gave me hope that I could get better but I still didn't know if I should have a full dose. The Benadryl would help for a little while. I finally went home the the next day. I went to  ER and I couldn't still walk very well on my own.  On January 23, 2021 - t he ER.  The doctor thought if she gave me an EPI pen but thought I might have more problems with it. She said that if Benadryl was helping than to keep taking it. The doctor didn't give me a dosage. I went back to ER on the 27th  because I still was not getting better. I was taking Benadryl and I was taking inhalers and at first I thought I felt like my airway felt more open when I took these but it didn't last for long. I didn't know, without guidance, how to take the medication - how much and how often. I couldn't think straight. On the 27th, that doctor listened but he wanted to help me.  He gave me Steroids for 5 days and Benadryl on top of that. And gave me Ativan to help me sleep. I had been going without sleep - I didn't have any other adult watching over me after the 3rd or 4th day when I left my sisters' house. Before the second ER visit, I didn't know when my airway was going to close. I could feel my heart racing/beating even when I wasn't doing anything. My heart rate would spike up to 119 or 120 randomly. I felt like my heart was beating out of my chest. About 5 or 6 hours after the Steroids there was popping sound out of my ears. It was loud and happening a long time, I wasn't sure I could sleep but I wasn't as aware of my heart beating out of my chest either. I could finally walk that next morning after the Steroids. I was trying to play with my toddler even though I felt fatigue and felt like crud - but I could walk without feeling I would collapse. So I over did - I tried to take a walk to the end of the street and I couldn't do it. My back hurt so bad after that. When I would lay down, I could not get the heaviness in my back to go away. It hurt so bad. I had a lump in my throat ( a little lower than my throat). That was scaring me. I went to ER again  (third visit)  - 28th  or 29th - tests came back normal.  I think it was the 28th. On that night, I was still on prednisone and I couldn't sleep with the pain. They gave me aspirin in case it was a heart thing. The aspirin may have helped with back pain. I took my Steroid pill and Ativan and that was my first night's sleep. The next morning, I could walk and I started to get a lot more hope at that point. I think I took Ativan for a couple of nights and got some good night's sleep. I took the Prednisone for 5 days and I didn't feel anymore like I couldn't stand up or that I was going to fall or that I needed supervision anymore. After about a month,  I had enough energy to finally drive and go to the store. I had been scared to drive because of my symptoms before that. By mid February, I was able to drive out and I went to a couple of stores. At that point, I felt like I was going to get better.  I'm a single mom and have been doing everything on my own for 20 years. I was talking to the doctor's office and to the nurse almost every day when I was sick. I don't get sick and I don't ever have to ask for help. I was disappointed with the lack of help I received.
LAB_DATA: I had three visits to ER - On the 28th - blood pressure; chest x- ray EKG; Ultrasound in my neck  - all tests came back normal
ALLERGIES: Mild allergy to a couple of antibiotics - Penicillin - hives; Erythromycin - stomach pain;  Inhalation form of peanuts  in peanut butter- breathing  problem from that three days.

May 24, 2021 (Mon) feel a little better but neck is still swollen and sore. 50% motion back to turn my head to the right. Breathing better when laying down through my nose as well. SYMPTOM_TEXT: He became very confused about time, went into the bathroom to brush his teeth 2 days after his 1st Pfizer shot and would not stop brushing his teeth for 30 hours. His parents tried to get him to stop several times. He only stopped because his parents finally called 911 to have someone help remove him from the bathroom. His gums were bleeding and he was limping a bit from standing at the sink brushing his teeth for so long. He was taken to the ER, his vitals looked good overall but he was dehydrated. Hospital could not explain why he did that, what was happening inside his brain. He could also not explain why he did that when asked. Very upsetting for his parents and siblings who felt they had no control over stopping him. It was mentioned he might need a neurological specialist. He improved once home. Seems he got very confused about time, did not understand how long he had been brushing his teeth and could not be reasoned with. He mentioned in the car on the way home from the ER with his dad that he still needed to brush his teeth once home. This scared his dad and his dad took him to go eat a meal outside of the home and that seemed to break up the time loop in patient's head. When they returned home patient no longer tried to brush his teeth for a long period of time.

Patient is a 15 yo female with a history of anxiety, recent ankle sprain, and no other known medical history who presents to ED today after she developed persistent shaking movements after her COVID 19 vaccination today. Medical work up has been thorough and has resulted negatively, including blood work, UDS, CT Head. She has remained slightly tachycardic, though she has also been moving continuously for several hours. Her physical exam is notable for several indicators of psychogenic origin, including demonstrating variability in tremor frequency (head, legs and arms vacillating it variable rates over time), distractability from motor tasks (head or arms stop shaking when asked to focus on moving her legs, for example). Her speech has also been affected, but this is also variable and she is at times using only 1 word sentences and other times responding more completely. Certainly she may have suffered a psychological stress today as she is fearful of needles and has a history of vasovagal response and her mother notes recent overwhelm with school performance, though this is not unusual for her. If medical work up continues to be negative, it may be reasonable to conclude she is suffering a conversion disorder  "FINAL DIAGNOSIS: Conversion reaction after a Covid 19 vaccine. Patient To be transferred via ground ambulance."

71 yo R handed female PMHx of obesity, anxiety, depression, HTN, afib, and COVID infection who presented to ED on 5/15/2021 with stroke like symptoms. She presented with right sided weakness, facial droop and slurred speech. LKWT 5/15/2021 at 0430. Patient reported going to bed around 2300 the night before and woke up at 0400 that morning with right sided weakness. Her daughter noticed slurred speech and right sided facial droop. Denied chest pain, HA, dizziness, no vision changes and no history of CVA. Stroke protocol was called. Teleneuro consulted and recommended a MRI. CT head was unremarkable. She takes ASA at home and received Plavix per neuro recommendations. Of note, patient tested positive for COVID but denied any respiratory symptoms and she has received her first COVID vaccination. Patient was admitted to the hospital for further treatment and evaluation for suspected CVA. Neurology consulted. Continued ASA, Plavix and Statin. Allowed for permissive HTN. Patient with history of Atrial fibrillation, currently normal sinus rhythm on telemetry. CHADS2VASC 3-would benefit from AC if no contraindication. Unsure why she has not been placed on AC and patient stated he only had one episode of Afib. Chest XR showed No acute cardiac pulmonary findings. Patient refused to have MRI brain due to anxiety. She stated that she attempted to have a MRI before and even with medication for anxiety she was not able to. Echo showed normal EF, mild MR, AR, TR, no PFO noted.CTA head and neck showed right vertebral artery ends in PICA, no acute abnormalities.  Labs noted B12 4,268 cholesterol 231 total, HDL 52, LDL 152, TAG 134, HbA1c 6.2, TSH WNL. Patient was out of the window for tPA. She was given a large dose of IV Ativan for anxiety. She continued to have elevated blood pressures with nausea that required IV labetalol to maintain blood pressure. HTN could likely be due to her significant anxiety. Cardiology planned to follow patient after discharge to discuss AC medication. Patient initially tested positive for COVID on 2/2/2021 and was able to take patient out of isolation.  Dx: CVA

That night, starting around 11:00, I started getting chills and feeling abnormally fatigued and achy. Pretty quickly, the chills got really violent and I felt really bad; like I had the flu. I noticed I was having trouble breathing. I have had anaphylaxis in the past before this. I did have a fever, it was low. I was up most of the night - bad night sweats; hurt all over, couldn't sleep as I was really miserable. The next day, I took Tylenol - around 03:00 am, but the next day I couldn't get out of bed and I had really violent chills, fever, body aches and headache was coming and going. I was still having trouble breathing. I took one Tylenol twice that day - one in the late morning and one in the evening sometime. Two days post vaccination, I started feel less bad, I still had a bit of a headache and I still had trouble breathing - chest was really tight. I was very low energy. I finally contacted my doctor after four days with trouble breathing. He told me to take an Advil or Tylenol and thought it was allergic response to vaccine. I took an Advil. The tightness decreased a bit. Didn't go away but noticeably better. The tightness was just continuing. The next day all the news came out about J&J vaccine, I called the doctor to tell him I was still having chest tightness and trouble breathing and they told me to call my PCP because they couldn't get me in. I called my PCP and she called back 2 hour later and I had just seen her the day before the vaccine and everything was very good that day she had seen me with oxygen, etc. . I went and go a pulse oximeter at Target - it came back at 100% and it would vacillate between 90-100%. My oxygen seemed fine. I thought it was a mass cell reaction to the vaccine  - that's what I felt - and I continued to take Advil every so often. It was about a week post vaccine when the tightness in my chest finally normalized. I continued to have fatigue. I felt pretty bad for two weeks post vaccine - tired, blah, and flared up with my disease and run down but no trouble breathing after about a week.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My issues started with my second dose on the second day about 24 hours after , I began getting a low grade fever with chills and just not feeling myself but my real issue was my fluctuating heart rate. I thought it was from the fever , I was wrong.  My fever and chills were actually mild and stopped completely a couple days later, however my fluctuating heart rate continued for almost two weeks after.      I wear a smart watch and I always have , first a Fitbit and now I wear an Apple Watch 6 , so I know my numbers , blood pressure etc.  The fluctuating I was experiencing was NOT NORMAL for me , at one point my heart rate shot up to 204 bpm doing nothing and then would drop like a rock and then go back up again. I actually showed my husband so he can see because I could not believe it was happening, and just to make sure the watch wasn?t messing up I put it on his wrist and his was fine , so at that point I knew something was wrong.      We both watched as it would rise to all different scary highs back down , I did feel at times a little lightheaded and some chest discomfort but nothing bad at all as it wasn?t continuous but my fluctuating heart rate was scary so I decided to got the the emergency room. They did testing and said it was possible it wasn?t coming from vaccine but no way to tell so they sent me to a cardiologist.      I have to say as well that I do have all my data on my watch to prove from around the time after my shot my issues with my fluctuating heart rate began.  I excercise and eat right and have no underlying health issues and this was the scary part , so I felt it necessary to report it because I am sure I?m not the only person out there that this happened to. What about the people that don?t wear watches or they don?t know their normal numbers and weren?t aware of what was happening, that?s scary too

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up at 3:00 AM Friday 5/24 having chest pain near my heart and issues breathing. I sat up on the corner of my bed feeling dizzy. Every time I would take anything more than a light breath, I would get a tight pain on the left side of my chest, which specifically felt like I had blockage in my heart. As I sat on the corner of my bed I tried to control my breathing and started to rub the area as I was taking breaths. The sharp pain in my chest while taking normal / deep breaths lasted for a few minutes and I feared I was having a heart attack. After going away initially that night, I felt the sensation  in a less intense fashion again later on Friday night and once more got a slight tight feeling in my chest while breathing on Saturday. During the initial episode on Friday night, I also got a deafened noise in my ears as if they had to pop as if I was gaining altitude in a plane or something. I got up off my bed to go to the bathroom and sat to urinate in case I was going to faint. The deafened noise went away after about a minute or so and turned into a static / fizzy noise for another minute or two while I was in the bathroom.  (The static fizz sounds got louder as I put my chin to my chest for some reason.) I was also sweating profusely throughout this entire process.
LAB_DATA: N/A. Have yet to get checked out by medical professionals after the event.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient developed maculopapular uticarial rash day of vaccine that started on his lower extremities and progressed over a few days to include part of his trunk and his proximal upper extremities.  Parents gave benadryl at home. It began to self resolve 5 days after vaccine, with complete resolution on day 6 after vaccine.    Additionally, on day 5 following vaccine, the patient had one, isolated, episode of chest pain and SOB that lasted 2-3 minutes. Patient believed he was having a panic attack.  Patient's mother took BP during event which was 190/95.  Patient subsequently brought to ED where all his vitals were diffusely within normal limits including BP.  No persistent chest pain and physical exam unremarkable.  Troponin was obtained in ED and found to be elevated at 1951.  Patient was admitted, troponins were trended, and patient remained in stable condition without further adverse events, and was subsequently discharge home with diagnosis of suspected myocarditis.
LAB_DATA: Troponins were ordered and trended.  Day 5 post vaccine value was 1951.  Day 6 post vaccine value was 1928 and repeated later that day to be 995.  Patient had EKG that displayed sinus bradycardia.   Patient had echocardiogram that was within normal limits.
HISTORY: Patient tested positive for COVID in Dec. 2020.  Was asymptomatic

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient arrived at ED 05/03/2021 with slurred speech, left-sided facial droop, left leg weakness.  Per discharge summary by MD : Before January 2021 pt was quite healthy and working in a casino.  On January 15, she fell in the parking lot and was started on Ibuprofen (800 mg) and flexeril for pain control.  On mid-February pt received COVID vaccine and about 1 week afterwards she developed dyspnea on exertion associated with night sweats, poor appetite, dry cough.   She had multiple workup done in the clinic including PCR-SARS-COVID x 2, which on both occasions were negative.  She was found to have elevated inflammatory markers including ESR and C-reactive protein.    She subsequently presented to ER the first time on 3/23 and found to be febrile with temperature of 39.3, saturation of oxygen was 100% on room air.  She had a repeat PCR-SARS-COVID.  This is her third one, which was negative.  She was found to have elevated levels of RF,  ANCA, markedly elevated CRP (>150).  She had (B) temporal artery biopsy that was negative.  She was discharged with oral prednisone 20 mg a day.   When she seen by Dr of rheumatology in clinic a few weeks later, her prednisone was increased to 60 mg a day for 2 weeks, then reduced to 50 mg a day.   She presented back to the hospital (this admission) on 5/3/21 with slurred speech, left facial droop, and LLE weakness and left foot numbness.  MRI brain showed acute infarct of left corona radiata though Dr of neurology reviewed the MRI and felt that there is some abnormality in the right temporal region as well, which would explain pt's neurologic symptoms.   She was placed on aspirin and high-dose statin (LDL was 132).  Usual stroke workup was negative.  She was maintained on prednisone for her recent dx of vasculitis.   She subsequently developed severe pain of her left flank and subsequent eruption of a dermatomal rash, consistent with shingles.  She was started on Valtrex 1 g three times daily.  She was also started on neurontin with uptitrating doses.   She had persistent pain so Lidoderm patches were tried which improved her pain significantly.   Initially there was consideration of rehab placement though pt improved to a point that she was felt appropriate to discharge home.  However, pt's daughter, who would be caring for patient at home, is 6-month pregnant, and worried about pt's shingles and the risk of transmission.   Therefore pt was not discharged home but rather kept in the hospital on Valtrex with ongoing attempts at placement.  Pt ultimately finished 7-day of Valtrex.  The vesicles on her left back have all flattened and the area now is mostly a nearly confluent region of dark discoloration.   At this point we re-discussed with pt's daughter that since pt has finished a 7-day course of Valtrex and that her vesicles have resolved, there is extremely low risk of transmission, especially with standard hand-washing hygiene at home.  Pt is also quite independent at this time and would not need assistance from her daughter for ambulation/ADL.  Pt will also have her own room at home.  At this time, pt's daughter and family were agreeable to take patient home.   In retrospect, pt's "vasculitis" symptoms appear to have started in earnest about 1 week after she received her COVID shot (1st shot, she never received a 2nd shot due to severe symptoms) so it is possible that her vasculitis may have been caused/triggered by COVID vaccine.  Other possibilities (less likely) include high-dose Ibuprofen (though she took lots of this in 2010 after another fall) or flexeril, though the timeframe is a bit longer.   In any event, she was advised to avoid unnecessary medications, particularly NSAIDs and flexeril at this time until her clinical picture becomes clearer.  She should also never receive COVID vaccine again.

52 yo Female had symptoms of anxiety ( tachycardia, racing thoughts about vaccine) and hyperventilation syndrome ( tachypnea, paresthesia or tingling sensation on her fingers ) 14 minutes after receiving her 1st IM dose of Pfizer.COVID 19 vaccine.  She has no prior history of anaphylaxis but had adverse reaction to acetaminophen years ago when she felt nauseated , with tingling sensation of fingers but no associated angioedema or low blood pressure , no prior treatment with Epipen IM.  She occasionally have similar symptoms at home after work but milder as per her husband .   Other risk factors : she missed breakfast and did not bring food for lunch , or snack, took only coffee few hours before vaccine . She is taking medications for her menopause symptoms which she did not take today.   She received her 1st Pfizer IM  dose at 12:15 PM and 14 minutes later called the attention of the EMT and physician at vaccine clinic  that she had  stomach discomfort, felt nauseated , cold , with palpitations , followed by tingling sensations of her fingers.  She had no difficulty breathing or swelling of her throat, no hoarseness.  She denied  lip  swelling and throat tightness. She admitted she had racing  thoughts in her head.  She was at observation area and immediately moved to the close observation area via wheelchair. She continued to be alert and oriented, appeared pink , no near syncope but was breathing fast ( 20-22/min) with sigh breaths.   Initial vital signs showed stage 2 hypertension , 160/100mmHg ( MAnual BP) , HR 101/min,  SpO2 98 to 100% on room air, RR20-22/min.  She was afebrile.   Serial exams were done.  She remained  alert, oriented to place and person , clear vision, though felt ? dizzy? in the beginning, but improved after she was allowed to drink 1Tsp. of caramel syrup with water and ate a fig bar at 12:40 pm. She No focal weakness or deficits, but her distal fingers felt cold with paresthesia . HEENT: tongue appeared normal with Mallampati score 2. She did not develop stridor or hoarseness throughout observation.   VS  were repeated every 10 minutes , BP ranged from 140/ 80mmHg and later improved to 120-130/80 mmHg, SpO2 98% to 100%on room air, RR initially tachypneic 20-22/min but after she ate , drank water  and reassured  that her vital signs were improving , no strider , clear lungs to auscultation, RR improved to 16 to 18/min and HR in 70?s per min.  She was accompanied by female vaccine staff to the restroom to urinate, no incident thereafter and she and her husband verbalized she was feeling better  . Upon discharge home , she had resolved dizziness, resolving finger paresthesia , resolved sensation of coldness  when given a foil wrap and a shawl, On exam , remained alert and oriented , HEENT exam without oral-mucosal swelling , no facial angioedema, verbalized chest tightness resolved after knowing he lungs were clear to auscultation.   She did not develop stridor , appeared comfortable , with clear speech .  She did not develop angioedema and and no hives.  Tongue exam normal without angioedema. Eye exam normal.  Chest  clear breath sounds to auscultation, no wheeze, Heart Improved normal resting HR (70?s/min) , no murmur , good and equal radial pulses.  Distal Upper extremities perfusion normal , were warmer  to touch ( was cold initially )  , pink, and well perfused. Nausea and epigastric  pain resolved , She  was kept under close observation until full recovery. Since she did not have signs of anaphylaxis , thus she was not given  epipen auto injection.  She did not  develop stridor, no throat tightness ; her tachycardia resolved and her BP gradually improved to 130/80 mmHg) with rest and sustained improvement until time of discharge home with her husband . Approximate duration of observation was 80 minutes.  They were initially offered to go to urgent care if they elected to be observed elsewhere but they decided to stay behind until she felt improved and reassured that her exam and VS were improving.  She was  able to stand up, observed to have normal gait , was escorted to her car with no further incident.  She and her husband verbally agreed to have her condition reported to VAERS. They were advised to read and follow advise of Pfizer EUA handouts.  If her symptoms worse. ( difficulty breathing, chest tightness , pallor , dizziness , to call 911 and bring to nearest ER. They were also asked to follow up with their primary care provider to consider options available for the second COVID 19 vaccine and monitor her BP and symptoms suggestive of anxiety.  Follow phone call done, she did well after going home but the next day , more than 24 hours after vaccine was given , she felt chest tightness , was brought by her husband to Medical Center , patient verbalize her sus BP was 174 and DBP mid 90?s.  She did not recall any injected medication , was observed and sent home with symptom improvement .  Upon phone follow today, 5/25, she verbalized she is feeling better and resting at home.  She acknowledged high BP as describe as above but asymptomatic now.  She will follow up with her primary care physician on 5/26/2021.

The patient ate a banana and candy bar and stated she did not feel capable of pushing her cart to her car or driving home. She then stated she had a systemic tingling/itching feeling, was feeling drowsy, tongue felt fuzzy/possibly swollen and decided to lay down on the floor on her own accord due to feeling faint. Patient at one point closed her eyes and did not respond for several seconds and when she came too she consented to Epinephrine injection, which was administered intramuscularly into the right outer thigh. It wasn't chronic, but faded in and out depending on movement. This side effect was most acute for the latter half of Sunday and for all of Monday, 5/10. On Tuesday, 5/11 it had subsided enough that I felt I could resume my normal workout routine. On 5/11, I was able to complete my normal workout, even as some exercises (like standing crunches) made the chest pain/abdominal pain particularly acute. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am a very active fit person that has consistently exercised 6 days a week for the past 15+ years doing CrossFit style workouts and also a consistent runner (half marathon). My heart rate and blood pressure are always very low due to my active lifestyle. Normally my resting heart rate is in the 50's or low 60's and my blood pressure around 100-110/60-65. My health was great - I exercised, worked, was active with my kids, and never had any of these symptoms prior to the 1st dose of the Pfizer vaccine. Days 1-2 post vaccine, I only experienced sore arm, my throat became tight/raspier, and a little tired. A few days after 1st shot, I had a big heart palpitation that woke me from deep sleep and heart was racing/pounding in the middle of the night. Next couple days noticed heart was working really hard doing the simplest things like standing up, laundry, or walking up the stairs. Heart rate was faster, my blood pressure was higher at rest, and my left arm where I had the shot continually felt tingly/numb. On day 6, about 1-2 hours after working out while sitting at my computer working, I developed the most intense crushing chest pain, high BP, extreme fogginess/brain fog (couldn't see the words on the screen), nauseous, felt like I might vomit, light headed, my outer fingers in left hand couldn't function and type (they curled up), and thought I was going to pass out. I laid down and took a nap. Day 7, my overall body feels off with similar symptoms. Day 8, I tried working out again and ended up experiencing the same debilitating symptoms described above plus chills but worse which sent me to the ER. They ran a battery of tests (EKG, blood work, chest x-ray, abdominal ultrasound) to rule out a blood clot from vaccine or heart attack. All tests normal and sent home. Days 9-21 - overall body feels weak from head to toe, low energy, smallest movements make heart race/pound, chest feels achy (squeezing pressure at times), left arm is still tingly, brain fog is terrible, nausea off/on, appetite is off, losing weight, high BP for me (130-140/80-90's), dizziness, tighter/raspier throat, bra and pants feel like putting pressure on chest/stomach (so not wearing them), sitting can feel like compressing something so have to get up frequently, hard time focusing, and haven't exercised at all for 2 weeks. Exerting too much energy seems to make things worse. Aside from these regular symptoms, I keep having "episodes" where things get worse and feel like I may pass out.  I followed up with my doctor around day 12 and she ordered a 48 hr heart holter monitor and heart stress test. Day 22 (5/13) - another intense episode that sends me back to the ER (same symptoms described above plus a very painful lump feeling on left arm near where vaccine was given that developed couple days prior). Repeat blood work and chest x-ray. Day 23-31 (today), while my energy level has started improving and overall I don't feel as awful head to toe as before, I still have chest discomfort/heart racing with little exertion, higher BP than my normal, brain fog, sometimes feel like might pass out, left arm still tingly, and have noticed my feet turn bright red when I am standing (not even for a long time). Laying down seems to help relieve some of these symptoms. I have another follow up appointment with my doctor this week. There is no doubt, the vaccine triggered something in my body causing these symptoms. Now I just want to know how to treat it so I can get back to feeling 100% like myself before I had the shot.  I will NOT be getting the 2nd dose due to these extreme and alarming symptoms I have been experiencing for over a month now.
LAB_DATA: Urgent care 4/30/21 - did EKG (normal) and sent me to the ER to check for blood clot or heart issues ER visit on 4/30/21 - EKG, bloodwork, chest x-ray, abdominal ultrasound (all came back normal) Primary Care doctor appt 5/4 - follow up to issues.  Ordered 48 hr heart monitor and heart stress test (came back normal),ER visit on 5/13/2021 - bloodwork, urine sample, chest x-ray (normal) Have another appt with primary care doctor coming up 5/26.  She ordered a POTS table tilt test to see if the vaccine has triggered POTS since all my symptoms match it and I get the bright red feet.  I have not completed this test yet so I don't know the results.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine on April 6, 2021. My symptoms began 10 days later. It all started with upper back muscle aches, on the same side as the vaccine injection. At first, I thought perhaps I pulled a muscle at a workout class, however after the third day of fatigue, the pain started intensifying throughout my body. My knees, ankles, wrists, back, neck and head started intensely aching and turned to flu-like fatigue and a low-grade fever which rendered me bedridden and unable to sleep or move much.   On 4/21, I checked into urgent care where both my COVID-19 and influenza vaccines were negative, so I was instructed to go to the ER to be evaluated for possible meningitis. At the ER, I mentioned separately to both the doctor and a nurse that I believed my symptoms could be related to the vaccine, but they both promptly dismissed the idea and discharged me with a ?muscle ache.?  For two days I was in relentless pain, which left me basically moaning and crying for hours on end. Several of my previous gymnastics injuries from when I was in my teens had resurfaced. My knee swelled up so badly that I couldn?t walk, my previous fractured wrists started aching, my left foot became inflamed, ankles ached, and a rare skin disease I had when I was 19, erythema nodosum, large painful welts on the legs, also re-emerged.   On 4/23, I saw my primary care doctor who also dismissed the idea of my condition being vaccine-related and misdiagnosed me with a respiratory infection, prescribing muscle relaxers that did nothing to ease the discomfort. Three days later I went back in to see her after my condition worsened and she ran labs and suggested it could be an STD (it was not).   On 4/28, the pain was intolerable, and I checked into a different ER where they admitted me to the hospital, ran labs and kept me overnight because my heart rate was so high. It was at a different hospital where the Infectious Disease doctor, finally diagnosed me with having a severe allergic reaction to the COVID-19 vaccine and told me that he had seen other similar cases. I was discharged and put on Dexamethasone.  My steroid dose ended on 5/3, and one day later, I started experiencing violent sickness along with the same arthritic symptoms as before, so I checked back into the ER where my knee was drained because there was worry of infection (it was not infected) and I was put on a longer, tapered course of steroid (prednisone) and referred to a Rheumatologist who ruled out autoimmune diseases and confirmed this was a reaction to the vaccine.  I finished the second round of steroids last week and am experiencing the same symptoms all over again, swelling and inflammation of the knee, severe pain in the right psoas, right toe pain, severe neck aches, and sleepless nights. I wanted to avoid a third round of steroids but couldn't endure the pain and swelling and it got to the point where I could barely walk or move, so I'm back on a third course for 15 more days. In the meantime, I am seeing a naturopath and a Traditional Chinese Medicine Doctor in hopes that they can provide more support than what I've been given elsewhere and that I can get back to  work and to living a normal life again.
LAB_DATA: I have pages and pages of test results from my visits in the ER on 4/28 and 5/4, as well as on 5/17. I am happy to provide these if needed. All tests for autoimmune diseases came out normal.  What was flagged for me was the following: C reactive Protein on 4/28 was 167 ESR was 21mm on 4/28 White Blood cell count- 11.9

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I began having strange heart palpitations in the late afternoon, 5 days after receiving the vaccine. On the morning of the 6th day, I had an elevated heart rate, chest tightness and shortness of breath. It was difficult to have a conversation without having to constantly stop to take a deep breath, to ?catch up.? My lungs felt like they had substantially less capacity with a deep breath than before the symptoms presented. I had extreme fatigue, joint and muscle pain. On the 7th day, I woke up with the same symptoms, and decided to go back to bed due to continues extreme fatigue. After waking up, I felt somewhat better, until later in the evening, when all the aforementioned symptoms came back. The following morning (8th day) I felt much better, and decided to go on a mountain bike ride to see how my heart and breathing felt. I noticed some decreased cardiovascular performance, but not as bad as the previous days. Later that evening, the shortness of breath and elevated heart rate came back. On the 9th day, the elevated heart rate was noticeably better, and the shortness of breath was still present, but not as bad as before. My blood pressure remained elevated and I have been unable to get it below 135/80 range. Same issues on the 10th day. Today, on the 11th day, I attempted to go run and found that my cardiovascular conditioning was the worst I have ever experienced in my life, without exaggeration. I had difficulty with a pace and duration that I would normally complete with ease before being vaccinated. I had to cut it short, as I was having difficulty breathing and my lungs were burning. I hope that these symptoms subside and are not permanent. I was hesitant to get the vaccine for a very long time, but decided to do it based of off removal of the mask mandates for vaccinated personnel. If I could go back knowing I would feel this way, I would never have allowed this vaccine to be injected in my body. I am a healthy, athletic 31 year old male, and now I feel like I am in the worst shape of my life. I feel awful.
LAB_DATA: None. The facility on base did not want to see me and run any tests ?unless the symptoms got worse.?

Hands Feeling Numb; Itching all over body; Feet Feeling Numb; Hands would Tingle; Initial Report Received on 31-Mar-2021  A 38-year old female certified pharmacy technician (race and ethnicity not provided) reported that she received HEPLISAV-B (hepatitis B vaccine) for hepatitis B immunization and developed itching all over her body, but mostly in her hands and feet, feeling numbness in her hands and feet, and tingling in her hands.  No relevant medical history or drug allergies were reported.    No relevant concomitant medications were reported.    On 23-Feb-2021, the patient received the first dose of HEPLISAV-B (Lot # 033093, expiration date 11-Apr-2021 and NDC # not reported) to the left deltoid. The patient reported no adverse reactions to this dose.   On 30-Mar-2021 at around 1100, 36 days after having been vaccinated with HEPLISAV-B, the patient received the second dose of HEPLISAV-B (Lot # 934600, expiration date 28-Feb-2022, NDC # not reported and serial number 334287615870) to left deltoid. At about 1930 the same night, the patient started having itching all over her body. While she was sleeping, she woke up about three times with her hands and feet feeling numb and reported that her hands would tingle. The patient reported that she does not have a rash, and while she stated that the itching was all over her body, it was mostly in her hands and feet.   At the time of the report, she had no further complaints of numbness since waking up that day. Her doctor advised her to take Claritin (loratadine) 10 mg and Benadryl (diphenhydramine) 25 mg three times daily as needed for itching.   No additional information was reported.   Company Comment:  The company assessed the events as non-serious.; Sender's Comments: The company assessed the events as non-serious.

I got the shingle shot,than a few years after that got the shingles/ Suspected vaccination failure; I got the shingle shot,than a few years after that got the shingles; Cannot describe the pain for 8 weeks; This case was reported by a consumer via media and described the occurrence of suspected vaccination failure in a patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingles vaccine) for prophylaxis.   On an unknown date, the patient received Shingles vaccine. On an unknown date, several years after receiving Shingles vaccine, the patient experienced vaccination failure (serious criteria GSK medically significant), shingles and pain. On an unknown date, the outcome of the vaccination failure and shingles were unknown and the outcome of the pain was recovered/resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the vaccination failure, shingles and pain to be related to Shingles vaccine.  Additional details were provided as follows: The age at vaccination was not reported. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Second dose not given; it was like if periaureal area felt some numbness; there was no visual swelling just the feeling of swelling and numbness; Flushed; Sweaty; possible allergic reaction; Allergic reaction with angioedema secondary to IM drug and Covid-19 vaccine; the top of her lip was numb; This spontaneous case was reported by a nurse (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of ANGIOEDEMA (Allergic reaction with angioedema secondary to IM drug and Covid-19 vaccine) in a 79-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 011M20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     Concurrent medical conditions included Allergy to vaccine (Allergy to Hepatitis B vaccine.), Psoriasis, Chest pain and Sinus disorder NOS. Concomitant products included VITAMINS NOS for an unknown indication.    On 04-Feb-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 02-Feb-2021, the patient experienced HYPOAESTHESIA ORAL (the top of her lip was numb). On 04-Feb-2021, the patient experienced ANGIOEDEMA (Allergic reaction with angioedema secondary to IM drug and Covid-19 vaccine) (seriousness criterion medically significant), HYPOAESTHESIA ORAL (it was like if periaureal area felt some numbness), VACCINATION COMPLICATION (there was no visual swelling just the feeling of swelling and numbness), FLUSHING (Flushed), HYPERHIDROSIS (Sweaty) and HYPERSENSITIVITY (possible allergic reaction). She was very very frightened to take it, she reacts to things strangely, when she has any procedure, they always say they never had that happen to anyone, she was allergic to antibiotics, different things happen when she takes different things, she was nervous about the whole thing, which may have to do with it. POSSIBLE SMALL STROKE; POSSIBLE TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (TIA); SUPER DIZZY; THROWING UP; COULD NOT OPEN EYES; WIERDLY AND EXCEEDINGLY THIRSTY; COULD NOT WALK; NUMBNESS IN LEFT ARM; COULD NOT STAND; HEAVINESS IN LEFT ARM; NAUSEOUS; HEADACHE; FELT LIKE HAD CHILLS LIKE ONE GETS FROM THE FLU; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 60 year old White, Not Hispanic or Latino female. The patient's weight was 175 pounds, and height was 65 inches. The patient's concurrent conditions included slightly elevated blood pressure, alcohol user socially and on weekends, non smoker, and penicillin allergy since childhood. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, intramuscular, batch number: 1805022, expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, 1 total, administered on 08-MAR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included valsartan for elevated blood pressure, acetylsalicylic acid, and furosemide.  On 10-MAR-2021, the patient felt like having chills like getting from the flu, for couple of hours might be, a headache for several days, might be for 3 days. For that the patient took some Advil 200 mg every 6 hours for the first couple of days. Then that passed and felt fine. On 24-APR-2021, around 04:00 in the morning the patient woke up and felt weirdly thirsty, exceedingly thirsty and super dizzy, nauseous thought was having a heart attack and heaviness and numbness in left arm but could still move the arm, however could not walk and could not open eyes until was in hospital. I received my Moderna COVID vaccine on Thursday, May 20, 2021 and at that time I only had a slight fever and my arm was a bit sore at the injection site.     My reaction to the Moderna began in the wee hours of Friday May 21st.  I had a fever of 103.0, I did not go to walk in or my doctor because I took Tylenol and after a few minutes my fever subsided.  I went back to sleep.  Upon waking up I had body aches, a running fever, my head felt like I was in a fog that I couldn?t shake.  I was so tired that I could hardly keep awake.  My fever kept getting worse through out the day so I kept taking Advil (I had stopped taking Tylenol because it had stopped working).   Advil helped a little bit but I felt like my fever would never go away.   This happened through out the entire Friday May 21st.  Then in the middle of the night around midnight Friday into Saturday I began sweating profusely all the while having a fever and body aches and I was really really tired.  When I woke up at 5am Saturday my clothes were drenched in sweat and I felt better, but the entire weekend I had nausea and diarrhea.

On the first day of the adverse effects I woke up to a rash on my legs. It was minor and I thought nothing of it. On the second day it had spread to my arms and was now a serious irritation. I rubbed Aloe Vera on it and that helped a little but wore off in an hour. By day three the rash was now spreading to my chest but I still wasn't sure if it was the vaccine. I took some Benedryll as an antihistamine and the rash completely dissapeared within an hour. 24 hours later at the time I had taken the Benedryll the night prior the rash reappeared and I he only possible explanation is some sort of allergic reaction to the vaccine. I have been allergic to it consistently and if it doesn't dissapeared entirely without me needing to take Benedryll I will be very concerned. The rash when it is present covers almost my entire body, spare my groin, head, neck, and some of my chest and back luckily. It itches very badly and constantly, and is very much visually present in large red splotches.
LAB_DATA: None so far, I am hoping it will go away and taking Benedryll works perfectly.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few hours after the vaccine, began having a headache.  The next day had severe body aches and chills, which continued for another 4 days.  I missed 4 days of work.  I began feeling better a week after the vaccine.  24 days after the vaccine, I was awaken with excruciating pain in my left abdomen, and had severe diarrhea.  The diarrhea lasted most of that day, the pain continued.  I went to an Emergency Room on 4/1/21, and a CT scan revealed what appeared to be a stomach ulcer, a kidney stone and a post-menopausal ovarian cyst, all of which were causing the pain.  I have been through many tests and seeing a variety of doctors, and currently am awaiting results and treatment plans for the stomach problem and the ovarian cyst.  The cyst has grown and is causing continued pain.  The stomach issue is being treated with Sucralfate 1 g 4 times per day and Pepcid 20 mg.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received second dose of Moderna COVID 19 vaccine at 10AM Thursday 05/20.  T+12-18hrs: Feeling flushed. Slightly confused. Body aches build over the night. Wake up with mild/moderate pain in back, knees, arm. Groggy. Went to work on something with a friend at 10:00 AM (T+24Hrs), but had to return home because....  T+24hr: ....headache growing. Went home and found fever at 102�.  Slight chills, bit mainly just heat without sweating. Fever hit 103.2 at peak. Went through 10lbs ice to keep the fever in check. Headache from T24hr-T36HR feels like a spike through the top of frontal lobe to my left eye.  T+32hr: Headache still intense. Only back pain now. Appetite slowly increasing.  T+48hr (Saturday morning). Back pain persists, but mild. Headache gone. Have a relatively normal day.  T+60hrs (Sat. Afternoon): Back pain increasing. Stop all unnecessary lifting/moving.  T+68hrs (early Sunday morning): Go to ER with the back pain. Absolutely excruciating spasms from top of sacrum - roughly LI/12T. Lower back stiff as wood. Given shot or Toradol, dose/prescription to flexiril. I specifically request this plan because usually takes care of the spasms; basically, get me able to move and the pain/spasms will go away.   NOTE: I have a history of back issues in this area, but I have not had an episode in years and certainly never had an episode that works like this with no relief. From about 2017-2019, I r  T+70-78hrs: Feel normal.  T + 78-88hrs: lower back pain comes back with an absolute vengeance.  T+90hrs (early Monday morning): Return to ER. Back pain worse than Sunday morning. Receive toradol shot and prescription Prednisone. Back pain gone by around 10:30 AM. Decide to take prednisone Tuesday morning as its getting a bit late in the day by the time pharmacy fills the prescription.   T+90hrs: Back pain returns in similar fashion as Sunday afternoon. Still. Barely mobile.   T+96 hours: Wake up with lower back pain similar to Sunday/Monday morning. Took prednisone and flexiril this morning.   Please help me.

Went in to physician due to shortness of breath. Found pericarditis.  The physician went in to do a pericardial window and the patient experienced bleeding so the surgeon had to perform a sternotomy to determine where the bleeding originated. Once the chest was opened the surgeon noted a mass that appeared to look like a fungus on the heart. Biopsy of the heart mass, pericardial fluid and a mass on the liver were performed.  The biopsy results originally came back as adenocarcinoma of the urinary (bladder, kidneys) origin. The physicians noted that that would be highly unlikely since there were no tumors noted in the urinary area.  Pathology was sent off again from the pericardial fluid that was obtained by "extracting RNA from tumor enriched sections.  This pathology showed the cells to be squamous cell carcinoma with 90% probability of coming from the lung. The doctors are finding this very unusual .  My husband was very healthy prior to this with no symptoms.  Could this be caused by the vaccine?

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day after, I had the normal fever, flu-like symptoms, and my left ankle/right knee ached pretty badly. Starting Monday 05/17, my right knee was unbearably painful. If I moved it at all away from a ~30 degree angle, my entire leg lit up with the worst pain I've ever felt. Not as bad as if I put pressure on it though, that was even worse. I couldn't walk, couldn't drive, could barely get out of bed for days. I got through that with over the counter pain killers and Biofreezing the knee like crazy.  Starting Friday 05/21 I believe, my knee pain suddenly went away only to be replaced with pain in my left foot. It's not nearly as bad as the knee was, but the entire left side is in constant pain made worse with pressure. I can drive now that my right leg works fine, but still can't walk without some form of assistance. I was reporting all of this in the V-safe health checker, but it apparently doesn't care outside of 7 days. Tempted to put "permanent damage" for Item 21 as the result, but I'm hoping this goes away soon.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: He got his vaccine, he had no reactions.  The next morning he woke up his arm was sore, and it was that was for 2 days.  Then his breathing starting getting worse.  He started coughing, couldn't lay down, could not sleep due to that.  He went to the ER and they told him that there was nothing wrong and that it was just allergies.  They told him to go home and take some OTC cold medicine and that everything would be okay.  A week later he went to another ER for the same thing as he continued not to be able to breath, they did a bunch of tests and said that nothing was wrong and that it was just a call.  He then went to Hospital ER and they released him stating it had just a cold.  He then called his cardiologist and they told him to go back to Hospital, was admitted on 5/11/21 and they did more tests and said that he had a blood clot in his left lung and said that it had nothing to do with the vaccine.   He was discharged on 5/13/21.  They put him on Heparin while in the hospital and sent him home as a disgruntled patient.   They also told him that he had fluid around his heart and gave him medicine to get that taken away.  They sent him home on Lasix and Eliquis.  He then went to another hospital on Friday 5/14/21 as he was going crazy about the blood clot and went there and was kept there for 3 days and discharged on 5/16/21 with the same medications, Lasix and Eliquis.   He was also told that he had fluid around his heart again.  Before the vaccine he was very healthy, and was able to jog around his neighborhood and now he's not able to do so, and they told him that he was now having heart failure and is having trouble breathing because his heart is swelling up. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received the Pfizer vaccine in the morning, then woke at about midnight. He went to get a drink of water, and was holding a glass of water in his hand. He started to feel as if the room was spinning, became very sweaty, had ringing in both ears, and lost consciousness, striking his head on the counter. The event was unwitnessed. He reports waking approximately 1 hour later with a bad headache. He had a headache and felt disoriented. He denies urinary/bowel incontinence or tongue biting. He was able to walk back to his room without difficulty, took ibuprofen, and went back to sleep. He woke the next morning with nausea and vomited, but this did not impact his headache. He has not had any notable neurologic symptoms since that time, but continues to have a minor headache. He has not had any further vomiting. Headache has not subsequently woken him from sleep and does not worsen with recumbent positioning. He denies visual changes, memory changes, difficulty swallowing, shortness of breath, ringing in his ears, or dizziness. He says his headache is located mostly around his forehead and at the top of his head that is now mild and feels like pressure ?like a tension type headache.? His mother is a nurse, and evaluated him the next day. The family did not feel that he needed to be seen in the emergency department, or prior to this visit. He has not had any previous episodes that were similar. Patient was evaluated in my clinic. Complete neurologic exam was within normal limits. He has been referred to neurology for further assessment.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had COVID in early December 2020.  I waited a few months to get the vaccine.  I was fine the day of the vaccine 16 MAR.  I took the next day off 17 MAR  because I was running a fever and and had body aches.  I did not have any alcohol on St Patty's day.  I pretty much slept the whole day.  I went back to work on 18 MAR and was feeling better with only a mild ever.  The night of 18 MAR I began to run a fever and had body aches.  The body aches worsened during the night I could not sleep.  The body aches became centralized in my upper back and shoulders,  My neck was hurting too.  I began to feel chest pains.  The chest pains increased in intensity.  I researched the symptom's which suggested I was having a heart attack.  I took some aspirin to try to alleviate the pain.   The pain continued and more severe so I drove myself to hospital. The staff  gave me an EKG and took blood samples for testing.  The EKG was normal.  The blood test came back with elevated levels of Troponin.  The Dr.  advised that the Troponin level indicated that I probably had a heart attack. the first hospital did not have a cardiac unit so I was transferred to  downtown location.  The staff there ran more test.  The EKG was again normal and the Troponin elevated so a Coronary angiography was conducted with catheter and dye.  The angiography was also normal with no sign of a heart attack the doctor said I probably had a reaction to the vaccine.  He suggested that I still get the second vaccine.  I did  get the second vaccine. After the second vaccine I only had fever and body aches, I pre0-gamed with aprin  and plenty of rest for the second vaccine.
LAB_DATA: EKG normal Elevated levels of Troponin Coronary angiography- no heart attack

According to the Centers for Disease Control (CDC), you can stop self-isolating if you meet the below criteria   If you will not have a test to determine if you are still contagious, you can leave home after these three things have happened: o You have had no fever for at least 24 hours (that is 24 hours of no fever without the use medicine that reduces fevers) AND o other symptoms have improved (for example, when your cough or shortness of breath have improved) AND o at least 10 days have passed since your symptoms first appeared   Managing your symptoms During this viral illness, rest and hydration are important in your recovery. You can take anti-fever medication as directed per your healthcare provider and package instructions.  Prevent the spread of illness  Separate yourself from other people in your home As much as possible, you should stay in a specific room and away from other people in your home. Also, you should use a separate bathroom, if available.  Call ahead before visiting your doctor If you have a medical appointment, call the healthcare provider and tell them that you have or may have COVID-19. This will help the healthcare provider?s office take steps to keep other people from getting infected or exposed.  Wear a facemask You should wear a facemask, if possible, when you are around other people (e.g., sharing a room or vehicle) and before you enter a healthcare provider?s office. If you are not able to wear a facemask (for example, because it causes trouble breathing), then people who live with you should not be in the same room with you, or they should wear a facemask if they enter your room.  Cover your coughs and sneezes Cover your mouth and nose with a tissue when you cough or sneeze. Throw used tissues in a lined trash can; immediately clean your hands as described below.  Clean your hands often Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds. If soap and water are not available, clean your hands with an alcohol-based hand sanitizer that contains at least 60% alcohol, covering all surfaces of your hands and rubbing them together until they feel dry. Soap and water is preferred if hands are visibly dirty. Avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth with unwashed hands.  Avoid sharing personal household items You should not share dishes, drinking glasses, cups, eating utensils, towels, or bedding with other people or pets in your home. After using these items, they should be washed thoroughly with soap and water and dried before use by others.  Clean all ?high-touch? surfaces every day High touch surfaces include counters, tabletops, doorknobs, bathroom fixtures, toilets, phones, keyboards, tablets, and bedside tables. Also, clean any surfaces that may have blood, stool, or body fluids on them. Use a household cleaning spray or wipe, according to the label instructions. Labels contain instructions for safe and effective use of the cleaning product including precautions you should take when applying the product, such as wearing gloves and making sure you have good ventilation during use of the product. By this morning (5/25), the swelling has reduced significantly and localized to the left front armpit. Mild pain remains, now more localized to the lymph node under the left armpit.

Burning/blistering rash developed abruptly on left arm, chest, lower legs and right arm that has continued to spread to entire body including lips and inside of nose. Numbness in hands and feet. Notes from all medical visits below. 5/17/2021 Walk-In. Patient present with a worsening rash x today.  She received her second Pfizer COVID vaccine on 5/14.  Patient reports a small rash at the vaccine site that evening.  No worsening of rash over the weekend.  Patient denies fevers, HA, ST, dyspnea.  She reports a history of skin sensitivities.  No new soaps, lotions or detergents.  No new medications or supplements.  No itching or pain from rash.  She reports that her symptoms started with small, clear, "bubbles", then turn into flat, excoriated erythema. 5/19/2021 SMHC ER. 32 y.o. woman presenting with a rash.  Patient had her second COVID-19 vaccine on 5-14.  On 5-17 started developing a rash over her left arm at the site of the vaccine.  Started with clear bubbles, that then look excoriated.  She reports that they feel like they are burning.  They have since spread to her chest and her back, her legs, her arms.  She has put a little bit of antibiotic ointment on some of them, but this has not helped. No painful urination.  Does report her eyes and her mouth feel dry. 5/19/2021 Dermatology Pt arrived from the ER admitting to significant fatigue. The burning in her skin has an abrupt onset which wakes her from sleep. She notes that starting Saturday 5/15 she has had intermittent pins and needles in her hands and feet. As of today her right foot is becoming more numb. She also notes the onset of burning at the left inside of her mouth. 5/20/2021 Dermatology. Assessment and Plan: 1. Neoplasm of uncertain behavior of skin. 32F with vesicular - petechial eruption with secondary crusting at trunk and extremities s/p 2nd Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine on 5/14/21. Vasculitis vs DIC vs Stevens Johnson syndrome/ TENS in pt with symptoms consistent with coronavirus infection despite vaccination. SURGICAL PATHOLOGY TISSUE SPECIMEN; pending. Skin biopsies sent urgently on 5/19/21 for H&E and DIF. Prednisone started 5/19/2021 in ER: 60mg x3 d, 50mg x 3 d, 40mg x3 d, 30mg x3 d, 20mg x3 d, 10mg x 3 d (18 day taper). Out of concern for possible vasculitis compromise of the pt's kidneys I prescribed bleach baths and topical mupirocin oint rather than add systemic antibiotics for secondary infection of lesions. Given the worrisome and worsening presentation, the pt and her husband agree to present to the E.R. They declined transport by ambulance and will go to the E.R. now. Number and Complexity of Problems Addressed. 1 acute or chronic illness or injury that poses a threat to life or bodily function. Mild headache last evening, no blurry vision. Extreme fatigue with effort of getting up and getting dressed Interrupted sleep with persistent burning pains at LEs, pins and needles at hands and feet and worsening blue discoloration at LEs and numbness at 2nd & 3rd rt toes. Has been able to hydrate; urine light yellow. Appetite maintained but no stool since 5/17. Pt removed IV from rt antecubital which had been left by E.R. 5/20/2021 ER. This is a 32 y.o. female  with a rash that initially developed over her injection site from her second COVID vaccine received 6 days ago.  The rash begins as bubbles and then appears excoriated.  Described as burning and have since spread to her chest, back, legs and arms.  She was evaluated yesterday at SMHC ED and Dermatology.  Placed on 60 mg Prednisone and admits that the pain has not really improved.  Sent here today for concern of DIC/Vasculitis/SJS. Patient well appearing, VSS. Will repeat labs, provide 1 L NACL and Oxycodone for pain. Had today's dose of Prednisone. Does have decreased DP pulses, foot mottling and decreased capillary refill.  Will obtain bilateral arterial US. Discussed with Dr. who also evaluated the patient and is in agreement.    Labs improved from yesterday, only mild elevation of D-dimer.  Some protein in her urine. Repeat evaluation after keeping her legs covered reveals normal cap refill less than 2 seconds.  Still mottled and unable to palpate DP pulses bilaterally. 5/21/2021 Assessment. Prescribed Ondansetron Hydrochloride 4 mg For nausea.

I received the second shot for my Pfizer vaccine on Thursday April 15, 2021. The weekend proceeding my shot I thought that I may be having some constipation so I took some collace and proceeded about my daily activities. I had a bloated feeling and felt as though I had gas that wouldn't pass. By Sunday I had a sharp pain at times when standing up or when I pressed the lower right side of my abdomen.  I didn't have pain on my left and also had discomfort around the navel area. I was able to have a bowel movement mid day Sunday and noticed that it hurt in my abdomen area to go (unlike when constipated) I also noticed that when I went to the bathroom I didn't feel the "relief" in my stomach that typically comes after you've been constipated and finally able to go. I  had no appetite and nausea. By Sunday evening the pain in my lower right abdomen became more noticeable and by Monday in the early morning ours I went to hospital where it was confirmed I wold need an immediate appendectomy for acute appendicitis.
LAB_DATA: CT scan confirmed that I had acute appendicitis on April 19th, 2021 and wold need an immediate surgery the same day.

Several weeks after my 2nd Pfizer Covid-19 vaccination I developed fingernail irregularities on my right hand, later diagnosed as Beau's lines.  I do not remember the specific date this appeared.  It started with purple/red color on four fingernails in the half moon area.  Later turned white and one nail came off, with another growing underneath. At some point the Beau's lines appeared.  By the time I got an appointment with my dermatologist, at the suggestion of my primary care doctor,  for diagnosis, significant time had gone by.  Around the same time after the vaccine,  I developed very painful headaches we are attributing to tight neck muscles, but I have never been a headache person before and these headaches are very debilitating  and unlike  any headache I have ever experienced, even though I have not been a frequent headache sufferer . I understand that Beau's lines have been associated with Covid iteslf,  but I highly doubt I had Covid itself.  I have had, in the past, very very rare side effects to medications and I have broken out in hives from the pneumonia vaccine  I had had before, several years ago.
PRIOR_VAX: Pneumonia vaccine

I believed it was a muscle strain. I did a cold compress, warm bath and took Tylenol from Friday to Saturday. I thought it got better but however by May 23rd, Sunday night I was incapable of walking on my own and needed assistance just to go to the bathroom. On May 24th I went to Urgent Care and they stated that I may have a blood clot so I went to the ER. While at the ER they stated I had a massive blood clot that would need a procedure done to remove it and was later admitted into the hospital and scheduled for the procedure. The blood clot travels from my groin to my ankle on my left thigh. They stated the reason for my blood clot would of been because of my birth control. And it?s possible reaction to me also taking the Pfizer vaccine. I have been on birth control for over 5 years and have not had any problems until now. I also do not have any history or family history of blood clots. I did not hit my thigh or have done any exercises for this to occur.
LAB_DATA: Blood work/ DDVT (tests to see if it is a blood clot) : result was abnormally high count.  Sonogram which solidified the presence of a blood clot and its extent.

After receiving my second dose, I was seen by my primary doctor for suspected Celiac disease (which came back positive). I had a strange medical episodes during the bloodwork (April 15th) that they originally assumed was anxiety. Symptoms were shortness of breath, lightheadedness, and loss of feeling in extremities. I?m a first responder and did not feel this was anxiety, but didn?t argue and forgot about it until it happened again.   I had my second episode on April 20th, and debated going to the ER for it. A third episode on April 23rd did put me in the ER. I proceeded to have more episodes on almost a daily basis after that and started monitoring blood pressure, pulse, blood sugar, and food intake at home (some of my bloodwork levels were off due to the celiac). I purchased a heart rate monitor, a blood glucose meter, and a smartwatch to monitor some of my symptoms. Both devices (monitor and watch) would later flag me as having a suspicious heart rhythm (heart monitor could be for fast/slow rhythm or for arrhythmia, smartwatch flagged me as Afib twice). I could not recreate these results when my husband wore the devices.  Episodes could be as brief as 45 mins or last more than 12 hours. I have a high pain tolerance and illness tolerance, and had to leave work several times due to my symptoms (extremely abnormal for me).   After several more appointments with my primary doc and another visit to the ER (where they did another EKG, an X-ray, and more bloodwork), things were still coming back inconclusive.  After about April 28th, I started having significant chest pain with my episodes. The ER checked me for possible clotting related to the heart issues and my birth control pills. My arrhythmia could not be captured on their devices.   My doctor has since diagnosed it as suspected myocarditis (pending more testing). We?ve ruled out all possible things related to my Celiac diagnosis, and can?t seem to find a cause for this. I had a few things I brought to her attention that may be the cause (pinched nerve at chiropractors, covid vaccine) and she says it may be the vaccine, and said I should report it to you.
LAB_DATA: EKG (twice). Once on April 23rd, once on may 16th.  Tons of bloodwork (clotting, hormones, lipids, sugars, and more) Chest X-ray, may 16th All came back as normal.   I am scheduled to get a holter monitor this Thursday and see a cardiac specialist in July for an echo.
CUR_ILL: On date of onset of symptoms (after second vaccine date), I was being seen for bloodwork related to a pending Celiac disease diagnosis (I have a long family history of celiac). We originally thought symptoms were related to that, but all tests since then have been inconclusive.

COVID-19 Navigator:  The person who will schedule you for your infusion, ensure your follow-up appointments are scheduled and that you have all the necessary tools to track your health.   Infusion Follow-up Plan:   Day of Infusion: o You will be discharged from the Infusion Center to home. o You will begin recording your temperature and oxygen levels (pulse ox). You will receive prompts from the monitoring program you selected. Follow the prompts for when to record your temperature and pulse ox.   Day 2-3 after Infusion: o You will receive a follow-up call from the COVID-19 Navigator to schedule your 7-day follow-up video visit with your Primary Care Physician.   Day 8-14 after Infusion: o You will receive a follow-up phone call to assess your overall health.   Day 15 after Infusion: o You will receive your final call from the Navigator, and you will graduate from the Infusion Program. You will resume your routine appointments with your Primary Care Physician.   When to call your Primary Care Physician: o Please call your Primary Care Physician if you have pre-existing health conditions that you feel need medical attention and are unrelated to your  COVID-19 diagnosis and symptoms.  o If you are experiencing non-life threatening COVID-19 symptoms and have additional questions.    When to call the COVID-19 Navigator:   o Please call the COVID-19 Navigator if you have general questions regarding the infusion you received today, questions concerning follow up appointments, or home monitoring procedures & equipment.  o You should receive a follow-up phone call from the Navigator within 2-3 days of receiving your infusion.  o If you do not receive a follow-up phone call, please call the Navigator   When to call 911 or Proceed to the closest Emergency Department: If you are experiencing life threatening COVID-19 symptoms including but not limited to: high fever, trouble breathing, persistent pain or pressure in the chest, new confusion, inability to wake or stay awake, blueish lips or face. How to Improve Your Breathing with COVID-19               Try to spend as little time as possible flat on your back! The largest part of your lungs are in the back of your body. When you lay on your back this causes fluid to pool in those parts of your lungs making it harder to breathe. Laying in different positions or sitting up will allow all the different parts of your lung to expand properly. You may notice it is easier to breathe immediately or soon after changing positions.                One of the best positions for this is called 'prone position' which is laying face down on your belly. This position makes it easiest for the biggest parts of your lungs to expand easily. This is called 'proning' and the more time spent proning the happier your lungs will be. Laying on your sides or sitting up in a chair is also helpful for breathing and changing positions helps keep your skin healthy.   Tips to Help with Repositioning ? Try placing pillows under the chest, hips, and lower legs when lying face down ? Trying different arm and leg positions can assist with comfort  ? Eat your meals sitting up in a chair when possible ? When laying on your side, a pillow behind you will help you not to roll on your back if you fall asleep ? If a position is too uncomfortable move on to another; comfort and rest are important parts of recovery ? Switch positions in a rotation to help all the areas of your lungs expand

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received his second Pfizer COVID vaccine Tuesday 5/18/2021.  On Wednesday started developing systemic symptoms such as chills, headache, myalgia.  Also developed constant sub-sternal chest pain.  Worse with movement or deep inspiration.  No clear positional component.   CP persisted until he came to the ED today.  Initial ECG showed concave ST elevations lateral leads.  Given his history this was felt to be most consistent with pericarditis.  He received toradol, morphine and SL NTG with near complete relief of the pain.  Repeat ECG showed resolution ST elevations.  Troponin was elevated, peak 9.08 ng/ml.
LAB_DATA: Cardiac catheterization - normal cornoaries. Mild distal anterolateral hypokinesis   Echocardiogram- normal LVEF 55%, no valvualar abnomalities, no effusion.
